title: caramels
directions: Cook the sugar, syrup, oleo and cream to fairly soft ball stage (244°).
Add vanilla and pecans.
Cool and let harden slightly. Wrap pieces in waxed paper.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook linguini according to package directions.
Cook carrots in microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
In large bowl toss together shrimp, linguini, carrots, pea pods and green onions. In a small bowl mix together the soy sauce, sesame oil, water, garlic powder, pepper and peanut butter.
Whisk until smooth.
Pour over shrimp
mixture and mix until all ingredients are coated.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Place
sugar,
flour,
salt and eggs in heavy saucepan. Beat with wooden spoon until blended.
Beat in half and half. Stir over
low
heat until mixture coats spoon and is smooth. (Do
not overcook.)	Add
melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat until	well blended
and smooth. Cool;	fold heavy cream into chocolate mixture to blend.
Fold in chopped chocolate. Freeze in
ice cream
freezer
or	pour
in chilled loaf pans. Cover airtight and freeze.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add oil, water, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: chocolate cola cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar and set aside.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix all by hand.
Store in covered container in refrigerator. Will keep 6 weeks.

title: fancy vidalia onions au gratin
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft, but not browned.
Mix together the flour, 2 tablespoons butter, egg, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add to onions and mix well.
This mixture will be "goopy" and sticky but will all melt together when cooked.
Pour mixture into a buttered casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup additional cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Best to use 1/2 Cheddar and 1/2 Swiss mixed for this casserole.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly, shortening, brown sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour and salt.
Cool in refrigerator until firm.
Roll into small balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in ground pecans.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Bake five minutes and remove and press thumb in each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 8 minutes.
Cool.
Ice with confectioners sugar icing.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix together cauliflower, broccoli, celery, walnuts and bacon in a serving dish.
Mix Miracle Whip and vinegar.
Add to salad and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Blend white sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add water and butter to first mixture and cook in a pan, stirring until thick.
Add vanilla.
This sauce will keep for months in the refrigerator.
Great over ice cream.

title: german peach shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Prepare German chocolate cake mix as directed on package except use 2 tablespoons less water.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Sprinkle loaves with confectioners sugar.
Serve slices of cake with sweetened whipped cream and fresh peach slices.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat cake mix, jello, eggs, oil and water for 4 minutes.
Pour into two loaf pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, lemon juice and rinds.
While cake is hot, pierce with fork, then pour mixture over cake.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, butter, vanilla, syrup, flour and salt in double boiler.
Heat.
Put pecans in bottom of unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Pour mixture over.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a large bowl; add oil, eggs one at a time, then add carrots.
Mix.
Bake in greased and floured pan almost an hour at 325°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Heat until cheeses are melted and serve with chips.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix in medium bowl with wooden spoon the yogurt, honey and lemon juice.
Gently stir in remaining ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage; drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and dry mustard.
Layer the cubed bread, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: velvet custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, milk and flavorings.
Beat again slightly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°. Turn oven down to 325° for 30 minutes longer.
Never fails if oven temperature is watched.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Slightly beat egg.
Add egg and milk; mix and drop by spoonfuls onto boiling broth.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Mix well.
Put in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 rolls.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, molasses and sour milk.
Add soda and spices to flour and add to first mixture.
Pour into two (7 x 11-inch) pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cajun deep-fried turkey
directions: Combine butter, onion paste, mustard, garlic, thyme, paprika, cayenne and chicken stock.
Using a syringe, inject mixture into turkey in many areas and depths.
Marinate 1 to 24 hours in refrigerator.
Heat oil to 375°.
Lower turkey into hot oil.
Cook about 3 minutes per pound.
Drain bird of excess oil.
Wrap in plain parchment paper or paper bags to hold the heat.
Place inside insulated cooler and let sit 15 to 25 minutes, until internal temperature reaches 170° to 175°.
Remove from cooler and wrapping.
Slice.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: wheat honey loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix dry ingredients together.
In separate bowl mix honey, buttermilk, vegetable oil and eggs.
Add to flour mixture and stir just until moistened.
Add pecans and dates or raisins. Turn into a buttered 8-inch loaf pan and bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes and turn out of pan.

title: carrot and cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; mix crushed pineapple plus juice and sugar.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add cream cheese; mix until dissolved.
Mix gelatin and pineapple mixtures together.
Cool until mixture begins to set.
Add the mayonnaise, carrots and Cool Whip.

title: overnite salad
directions: A 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan is needed.

title: frittata
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, brown onion in butter. Beat eggs with milk and seasonings.
Stir in rice, tomato and green chilies.
Pour in skillet.
Reduce heat to medium-low heat. Cook until top is set (12 to 15 minutes).
Sprinkle with cheese. Remove from heat and let stand for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix flour, apples and nuts and set aside.
Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together.
Put in flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh cherry pie
directions: Line a 9 or 10-inch pie plate with pastry.
Pit the cherries. Combine the cherries, flour, sugar and salt.
Fill crust with fruit mixture and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and pierce holes in the center.
Pinch the crust firmly together and crimp edges. Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 40 minutes longer.
Cool to warm and serve.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix flour and margarine as pastry, add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: olive dip
directions: Process olives very fine in food processor.
Add low-fat mayonnaise.
Process until smooth.
Add cottage cheese.
Process until smooth.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: yummy hors d oeurves
directions: Combine and spread over sliced bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fat free oatmeal bread
directions: Mix oatmeal, 4 cups water,
molasses and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and warm water mixture.
Add flour.
Dough will be sticky.
Let rise in bowl.
Spray bread tins with Pam and put dough in loaf pans.
Let rise.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: one of leo latimer's cakes
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together in mixer.
Pack into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and 3x sugar well; pour over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Arrange on large platter in layers as follows:

title: fast and easy bread
directions: Melt margarine in loaf pan.
While this is melting, mix other ingredients.
Pour margarine out of the pan and pour in dough. Pour margarine over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
water.
Stir
in
sugar
and salt. Blend in cottage cheese, butter, dill weed, egg, soda and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make
a slightly stiff dough.
Cover with towel.
Let rise in warm
place free from draft until doubled in bulk (about 1 hour). Stir
batter down.
Turn into well-greased pan.
Cover with waxed paper.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about
30 minutes).
Bake
at
for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain; cool.
Chop carrots, celery, onions and eggs.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and buttermilk. Sift together soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Add apples and mix all together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Add 2/3 cup sugar to 2 cups fruit (use any fresh or drained canned fruit or berries).
Set oven at 350° and put oleo in deep dish, approximately 6 x 10-inches.
Put in oven to melt.
Stir up batter of 3/4 cup sugar, 3/4 cup flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter over melted oleo.
Do not stir.
Then pour fruit over batter. Bake approximately 1 hour.
Batter will rise to top.
Brown and crisp when done.

title: old-fashioned bean soup
directions: Rinse navy beans and pick out the bad ones.
Place beans into the 11 cups of boiling water.
Boil for 2 minutes; cover and let stand overnight.
The next day, add salt and other ingredients. Gently boil beans in the same water in a covered pot for about 2 hours until tender.
Add more water as needed.
Remove fat, bone and skin from ham but leave the meat in.
Season to taste and simmer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk, vanilla and egg yolks in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened (about 12
minutes).
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Beat until it is spreading consistency. Can be spread on German Chocolate Cake. Can substitute chopped almonds for pecans.

title: easy baked chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, on top (may be skinless, if preferred).
Lightly salt and pepper chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours or 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: "the great dip"
directions: Beat until light and fluffy.
Chill overnight.
Serve with chips or vegetables.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef in large skillet, covered with water; cook until it turns grey
and all pink is gone.
Drain liquid and add taco seasoning and Ro-Tel.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
In long cake pan, put a layer of Doritos.
Cover with layer of cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Pour ground beef mixture over this, then repeat with another layer of Doritos and layer of lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Can be warmed in the microwave later.

title: whole-wheat soda bread
directions: Mix 2 cups white flour and 2 cups wheat flour and add raisins and caraway seed. Cut in butter. Combine milk and eggs; stir into dry ingredients. Turn dough onto board and knead in remaining 1/2 cup flour. Shape into 8-inch pancake. Place on greased cookie sheet. Mark an X on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: macaroni-fruit salad
directions: Combine lemon juice, flour, sugar and pineapple and fruit cocktail juice.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add eggs and heat again.
Cool slightly.
Add macaroni, pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, add marshmallows, whipped cream and grapes or cherries or mandarin oranges.
Serves 25 to 30.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix corn, Veg-All, mayonnaise and cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Mix butter and crushed crackers. Put on top and bake for another 10 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, except sugar.
Mix butter, oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add zucchini, buttermilk, vanilla, walnuts and chocolate chips.
Mix along with dry ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: microwave hot fudge sundae cake
directions: In ungreased pan, or glass casserole dish, stir together flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla.
Stir with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts.

title: orange cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package and bake in 3 or 4 layers.
Mix sugar, egg whites, orange peel and lemon juice. Spread between layers and on top of cake.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Mix together well.
Add egg.
Trim crusts from bread slices.
Roll each slice with rolling pin.
Spread with cheese mixture, 1/2 tip of asparagus and roll up.
Dip in melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 25 rolls.

title: pecan cookies(easy - makes 8 dozen)
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts. Drop by the teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sausage cake
directions: Bring to a boil 1 cup raisins and 1 cup water for 1 minute. Cream sugar and sausage, add spices, cherries, nuts and pineapple. Stir.
Strain raisins and add to mixture.

Add soda to raisin and cherry liquid and then to the mixture of sugar, sausage, etc. Sift flour and baking powder and add to mixture. Put mixture in a tubular pan (angel food cake pan), ungreased and drop a couple of times to make sure the batter has gone to the bottom of the pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Place pan upside-down on neck of pop bottle to cool.

title: betty freezor's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix in other ingredients and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add shortening.
Blend thoroughly.
Add milk.
Drop by tablespoon or roll out.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: heath bars
directions: Line a 13 x 9 inch pan with foil. Grease and spray, then arrange exactly 24 soda crackers on foil. Combine butter and brown sugar in a saucepan and boil for 2 to 3 minutes. Pour mixture over crackers and bake at 400° for 9 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over hot mixture. Spread chips as they begin to melt. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Place in refrigerator approximately 45 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix the Ro-Tel tomatoes and the cream of mushroom soup together in a bowl.
In a baking pan, place the pork chops.
Cover with chopped potatoes and carrots.
Pour soup mixture over this.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat.
Boil macaroni; drain.
Cover bottom of pan with sauce and meat.
Add layer of macaroni, sauce and cheese; keep layering until pan is full.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee punch
directions: Stir sugar into coffee and chill thoroughly.
Fold in whipped cream and ice cream just before serving.
Yield:
1 1/2 gallons.

title: bob's favorite barbecue ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces; place on a rack in broiler pan. Salt and pepper.
Place under broiler and brown on both sides. This takes away a lot of grease.
When the ribs are nice and brown, sprinkle with liquid smoke.
Place in a crock-pot and pour barbecue sauce over them.
Set the dial at low and cook for 12 hours.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, warm water and sugar; let yeast dissolve.
Stir to mix.
Add milk, oil and eggs (beat first); mix well.
Add 1/2 flour and salt; mix well.
Add enough flour to make a dough not real stiff.
Let rise for 1 hour or until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Knead in extra flour if needed.
Roll out and cut into rolls or pinch in muffin pans.
Let rise again for about 1 hour or until double in size.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut potatoes into large chunks.
Melt margarine in large baking dish.
Add cooking oil.
Add potatoes and cut up onion.
Stir to coat vegetables with oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Stir once during baking.

title: south of the border beef and bean cornbread
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown ground beef, onion and garlic together until onion is just tender; drain. Stir in salsa, taco seasoning and water. Reduce heat to low and cook 5 to 6 minutes, until mixture thickens.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Place in bottom of sheet cake pan the coconut and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions and pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, margarine, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Streak cream cheese mixture over cake and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream breakfast cake
directions: Beat the eggs until thick and fluffy. Add the sugar and oil and beat again. Blend in the cake mix, sour cream and nuts. Do not overmix. Pour half the batter into a well-greased Bundt or tube pan. Mix together the brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over the batter. Swirl in lightly with a knife. Pour the remaining batter on top. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes until cake tests done.

title: refrigerator banana pudding
directions: Combine vanilla pudding and milk. Beat until thickened.
Add sour cream.
Layer vanilla wafers, pudding mixture and Cool Whip. Repeat layers. Serve well chilled.

title: molasses apple butter
directions: Cook well, stirring all the time, until thick and buttery-like.

title: hawaii: luau sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine and combine with all ingredients, except nutmeg.
Spread into casserole dish and sprinkle on nutmeg.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Serve in individual cups or large shells.

title: clam dip
directions: Thin with a bit of milk if needed.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Blend oatmeal in blender to powder; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to this.
Mix in flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder, baking soda, chips, candy bar and nuts.
Roll into balls; place on cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: hanky panky
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage.
Drain, using a colander.
Melt cheese in a large skillet.
Add meat. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Spread on bread and freeze.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain, combine all other ingredients and mix with hamburger.
Cook on low for about an hour.
Serve.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: In bowl, melt butter; add mixture of flour and sugar. Add milk and salt. Add fruit (do not mix fruit in). Bake at 300° until brown. Crust will rise above fruit.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix pepper, salt and flour together.
Melt oleo, then add pepper, salt and flour.
Grate cheese and work with hands.
Use little star on cookie press.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: "heavenly hash" christmas candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and form into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin wax in a double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture, using a toothpick.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: mrs. fields chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to butter mixture gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Place golf ball size dough balls on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 112 cookies.

title: mom's hot dish
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Brown hamburger with some chopped onion and add.
Place in casserole and add the soup and beans.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated through.

title: chocolate angel dessert
directions: Work the nuts, flour and oleo as for pie dough.
Press onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer.
Spread in baking dish.

title: pineapple casserole(good with ham)
directions: Combine ingredients in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: never fails fudge
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and cook over low heat.
When it starts to boil, cook for 5 minutes while stirring constantly.
Into a large bowl break sweet chocolate (I use Hershey bars) and chocolate chips.
Add marshmallow cream and salt.
Pour hot mixture over chocolate and mix well.
Add vanilla and pour into well-greased pan.
Refrigerate.

title: friends cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter together.
Stir in noodles and nuts.
Let mixture stand a few minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture forms soft ball when dropped into cold water or 236° on candy thermometer.
Add vanilla, pecans and butter.
Place pan in cold water in sink; stir constantly until mixture thickens and loses its shiny appearance. Pour into buttered pan; cut when cool.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Place potatoes in a large pot and cover with water.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook until done.
Peel and dice cooked potatoes.
Place in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Combine cheese, pimentos, onion, green pepper, bread, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour over potatoes.
Drizzle milk over potato mixture and cover with cornflake crumbs.
Bake 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat broccoli until thawed.
Combine in a large bowl with rice and sour cream.
Saute mushrooms and onion and add to broccoli mixture.
Stir in 3/4 cup of Cheddar and 3/4 cup Monterey Jack cheese.
Stir well and pour into casserole dish. Top with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: chicken wild rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in kettle with water, sherry, salt, curry powder, onion and celery.
Bring to boil.
Cover tightly.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove.
Strain broth to save.
Cool chicken and bone.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: whole grain batter bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stirring until butter melts. Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in oats, 2 cups flour, eggs and nuts. Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to batter and mix well.
Use remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Place in a large greased bowl and let rise until double in size.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Add just enough water to all of the ingredients to be able to mix the dough so it will stick together.
Shape into desired shape of balls.
Dip into chocolate mixture of 3/4 stick paraffin and 12 ounces chocolate chips.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add to first mixture and blend well. Stir in last three ingredients.
Bake on greased cookie sheets in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: tater tots hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey and onion.
Stir together soup, celery and milk.
Add to meat.
Add frozen vegetables.
Divide into two 9 x 13-inch pans.
On top of each, add 1 1/2 cups cheese and 1 package Tater Tots.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered. Serves 20 people or freeze one pan for later use.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in gallon jar with tight lid.
Put 3 heaping teaspoonfuls in a cup; fill with boiling water.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Mix all other ingredients, except butter and crackers, with vegetables.
Place into buttered dish. Mix butter with crackers and put on top.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until bubbly so that onion and celery will be crunchy.

title: sausage dip
directions: Lightly brown meat and drain. Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Keep warm in electric skillet or crock-pot.
Makes 12 servings.
May be frozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until well mixed.
Add buttermilk, sugar, coconut, margarine and if desired, vanilla flavoring.
Mix well and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell or deep dish shell.
Cook for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy brownies
directions: Melt margarine over low heat; add cocoa.
Stir to blend.
Beat eggs; add sugar.
Beat well.
Stir in cocoa/margarine mixture. Add vanilla; stir in flour and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Soak wild rice overnight or for four or five hours; drain. Add ingredients; cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(May be made ahead.)

title: vanilla cake
directions: You will need a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: pumpkin or squash pie
directions: Mix egg yolks with pumpkin and milk.
Mix in flour and sugar. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: stewed chicken
directions: Steam chickens in small amount of water until meat falls off bones. Do not let water boil away completely as you will need it. Cook on low fire. Make a roux using the stick of butter and enough flour to take up grease. Add the onions to roux. Cook until onions are clear. Add remaining chopped seasonings and saut. Add chicken broth to make a gravy. Adjust seasoning salt and pepper. Pour gravy over deboned chicken (which has been placed in a large casserole dish). If needed, add more water. Cook in slow oven (250° to 300°) for 3 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer green beans, corn, water chestnuts and onion in a casserole dish.
Mix the soup and sour cream together; spread over top of vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese on top of soup mixture.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until bubbly and lightly brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter and sugars until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla, blending well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and pack into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 and 1/2 hours.
Yield: 8 servings. Carbohydrate 22 g, protein 23 g, fat 35 g, calories 500.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: super supper stew
directions: Put meat and vegetables into large, round baking dish (Dutch oven).
Spread soup over meat and veggies.
(No need to stir.) Sprinkle pepper over all.
Cover and bake for 4 hours at 275°. Remove from oven.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and make into small balls. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix together the first eight ingredients.
Bring the remaining ingredients to a boil.
Cool and pour over mixed vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in oven at 325° until hot.
Serve with crackers and/or raw vegetables.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and place in a 3-quart greased casserole.
Brown and saute celery, onions and peppers in 3 tablespoons sausage drippings.
Dissolve soup in boiling water.
Place all ingredients, except almonds, in casserole and mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out, stir and top with slivered almonds.
Bake until toasted.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked potato boots
directions: Bake potatoes in hot oven
for
hour or until tender.
Scoop out potatoes with
a
spoon being careful not to break shell.
Mash potatoes and
add
salt, margarine and milk. Mix well.
Put mashed potatoes
back into shell.
Sprinkle with bacon bits and cheese and put
back
in
oven for 20 minutes at 400° or until top is brown; cheese is melted.
Cheese and bacon can be left off.
Add anything
else, just plain butter on top, parsley, paprika.

title: quiche
directions: Beat the eggs together.
Add cottage cheese; beat with mixer until creamy.
Add margarine, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
It looks like cake batter.
Add cheese and whatever else you want in it.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; turn down oven and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy linguine with red clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in hot oil in medium saucepan over medium heat until golden brown, stirring constantly. Blend in flour. Gradually stir in juice from clams, parsley, wine, salt and pepper. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 2 minutes while stirring. Stir in Prego sauce and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Cook carrots and broccoli on High in microwave for 8 minutes (in a casserole dish). Pour corn over carrots and broccoli; layer on French fried onions and sprinkle with cheese. Heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: chopped apple loaf
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs and mix with oil.
Coat the apples well with this mixture.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Preheat deep fryer half full of oil.
Drain all but 1/4 cup of liquid off the salmon or tuna and set aside, then put the salmon or tuna in a mixing bowl and break it apart with a fork until you have no big flakes.
Add the flour and egg.
You may use a dash of pepper, but no salt.
Mix well.

Add the baking powder to the liquid that was set aside and beat well with a fork or whisk until frothy (this is an important step and this mixture can't "sit"). Pour into the fish and stir until well blended.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice, pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping.
Divide between the two pie shells.
Garnish with cherries.
Cherries may also be added to the pie mixture.
Chill until set.

title: cindy's cornflake candy
directions: Cook sugar and syrup on low heat until bubbly.
Mix in corn flakes and peanut butter.

title: health bread
directions: Measure the first two flours with yeast and set that bowl aside.
Measure rest into another and dissolve with the hot water. When lukewarm, add the flour with yeast in.
Measure in 4 cups flour and mix 1/2 minute on low and 3 minutes on high speed. Add more flour and work into a nice smooth dough ball.
Put into a pan to rise until double.
Push down.
Rise again to double.
Turn onto a pastry cloth or what you use.
Work some and divide into 3 to 4 loaves.
Place loaves into greased pans and rise again. Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for 45 minutes. Remove to a rack to cool. Makes 3 to 4 loaves.
(Yes, it is turned out of pan.)

title: mexican bean salad
directions: In large bowl, mix salad oil, lemon juice, chili powder and salt.
Gently stir in beans, green chilies and diced avocado. Arrange lettuce leaves on dinner plates; top with salad.

title: corn pie from chile
directions: In skillet, brown the beef with the onion and other ingredients.
Add 1 cup of water (cold) with 3 tablespoons corn flour; when it is cooked, spread into a Pyrex pie dish.
For topping, boil the corn for 5 minutes, then drain and mash in a food processor.
Spread mashed corn over the top of the meal. Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until a crust forms on the top.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix all together with beater.
Spread in pie plate and sprinkle with curry powder and paprika.
Slivered almonds optional.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken breast and dried beef
directions: Butter flat baking pan.
Sprinkle cut up dried beef in bottom of pan.
Wrap chicken breast in bacon.
Place on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Baste occasionally.
Do not salt.
Do not cover.

title: angel dessert
directions: Mix gelatin according to directions; add thawed strawberries and allow to congeal.
Stir in angel food cake that has been torn into small pieces.
Fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Combine milk, flour, salt and pepper. Batter cucumbers in meal mix.
Fry in shortening or oil until brown on both sides.

title: "good biscuits"
directions: Continue as you would with your own biscuits.
If you like, brush 'em with butter for Popeye's type biscuits.

After mixing the above, knead on a floured board (using some of the dry biscuit mix) and "pinch off" amount and place in a lightly greased pan. Cast iron skillets give your biscuits a good "crusty" bottom. Bake as directed on the box.

title: beef and cheese nachos
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add 1/2 cup of water and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Melt Velveeta over low heat (or microwave).
Add cheese soup and cook until smooth.
After hamburger has simmered, add cheese mixture and Ro-Tel and heat together.
Serve over tortillas and enjoy.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large Dutch oven, warm oil on low/medium heat. Add chicken pieces, cooking 6 to 8 minutes. Add all remaining ingredients, except vinegar. Cook on low/medium heat, covered, stirring every 30 minutes, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. In last 30 minutes, add vinegar. Serve over white rice or spaghetti. Serves 3 to 4.

title: fresh corn puffs
directions: Husk the corn; remove silk and scrape kernels and pulp from the cob.
If you use the frozen corn, thaw well before scraping. There should be about 1 1/2 cups corn and pulp.

title: dutch green pea soup
directions: Soak green peas overnight.
Cook meat with bouillon cubes 1 hour (when using bones, strain broth).
Add onions, celery, carrots, parsley, pepper and meat cut from bones.
Add green peas and boil at medium heat, stirring continuously, until the peas are soft and fully cooked.
Add the sliced smoked sausage.
Season to taste (pepper, salt, bouillon cubes).
Soup has to be thick. Serve with croutons.

title: poor man's fruit cake
directions: Boil together 20 minutes and cool.
Add flour (sifted with soda and salt) and eggs.
Add fruit mix and dates if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, salt, chocolate and corn syrup in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Cook slowly to soft ball stage (228°).
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add butter; cool mixture to 110° or lukewarm.
Beat in vanilla and walnuts on high for 3 minutes or until mixture is no longer shiny.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool. Cut in squares.
Makes 4 dozen pieces.

title: heritage grape wine
directions: Will also need 1 balloon and 1 (1 gallon) jug.

title: frosty strawberry cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Pour into 12 foil or paper-lined muffin cups.
Freeze until solid.
Thaw at least 15 minutes before serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Prepare fruit and mix with 1 cup sugar.
Preheat oven to 350°. Put margarine in very deep baking dish and set in oven to melt. Stir up batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit on top.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Combine sugar and 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir in rhubarb and spread mixture in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine 4 tablespoons butter, 2/3 cup flour and brown sugar.
Cut into crumbs with pastry blender or fork and spread over rhubarb mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with rich milk or cream.
Turns out something like an impossible pie.

title: pork chop dressing
directions: Boil chops in water in large pan until tender.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool.
Make corn bread according to package directions on package.
Save water that pork chops were cooked in.

title: old fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat the margarine and peanut butter until well blended.
If necessary, chill dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly; decorate with candied cherries, or flatten with fork dipped in colored sugars.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool on rack. Makes 6 dozen.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Top with 1/3 cup butter and 1/2 stack pack Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
May be made ahead of time and frozen without topping and baked later.
Very good.

title: cheesy spinach bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach until barely tender. Drain well.
Stir soup and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients to soup and sour cream mixture.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Cook brown sugar, water, flour and egg yolks until firm; add pineapple.

title: stuffed buns
directions: Grind all ingredients (except buns) together.
Hollow out buns; fill buns and wrap each in foil.
Heat in oven 1 hour at 250°.

title: banana-pecan bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, then beat in the eggs.
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add this dry mixture to the wet mixture.
Mix very well, then add the bananas and vanilla.
Stir in the nuts.

Divide the mixture evenly into two 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch greased bread pans and bake at 350° until the loaves are browned and a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean. This should take approximately 1 hour.
Remove bread from pans and cool.
Excellent!

title: fudge
directions: Mix milk, butter, sugar and marshmallows.
Cook until boiling; stir constantly for 5 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Take off heat and add chips, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish and let cool.
Use the pan you want that will give you the desired thickness you want.

title: overnight chicken
directions: Wrap bacon around chicken breasts.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with chipped beef; arrange chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours (uncovered).

title: candied cranberries
directions: Spread the cranberries in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cranberries with sugar; let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Stir, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Stir the cranberries occasionally by carefully lifting and turning the cranberries with a metal spatula. Chill until ready to use.
Yield:
3 cups.
Carbohydrate 11 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories per serving 44.
One tablespoon = 1 fruit exchange.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Shred cheese and mix all ingredients. Form into 1-inch balls. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown. Makes about 6 dozen. Sausage cheese balls can be frozen, uncooked.

title: black bean soup with sausage
directions: In 5-quart pan, bring beans to boil in 7 to 8 cups water. While heating, finely chop and add all other ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until beans are soft (add water if needed during cooking).
Stir, pressing spoon against side of pan to mash beans slightly.
Add garlic, cumin, oregano and hot pepper; cook another 20 minutes.
Cut sausage into 1/2-inch slices and add to beans; continue cooking just until sausage is heated through.
Salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with chopped onion, fresh chopped cilantro and/or sour cream.

title: surprise vegetable dish
directions: In large heavy skillet with lid, add olive oil, then chopped sweet potato and onions. Stir until coated with oil and add 1/2 cup water. Cover with lid and cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Place layer of graham crackers in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish (don't crush).
Mix the next 4 ingredients.
Pour small amount over crackers.
Do another layer of crackers and pudding, then another layer of crackers and pudding.
Chill.
Melt frosting in microwave; pour over pudding.
Chill again.
Can be served while frosting is warm.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in casserole dish in order.
Heat through in microwave. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts.
Drizzle can of condensed milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: healthy dip
directions: Blend together and serve with fresh cut vegetables.

title: savory baked ham salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, milk, mustard, salt and pepper; mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reserve 1/2 cup of cheese.
Mix well. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with reserved cheese; continue baking until cheese melts.

title: meringue
directions: Mix well.
Press in dish or pan and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: creamy raspberry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and condensed milk together.
Add lemon juice and Cool Whip.
Stir in raspberries and freeze.

title: steamed chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour and brown in margarine.
After all the chicken is cooked, return it to the pot.
Pour wine, shoyu, salt and pepper to taste.
Add the milk.
Cover pot and let it steam or simmer for 40 minutes or until tender.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Pour into pie crust, spread evenly.
Spread cherries evenly over mixture and chill.

title: cherry dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Mix sugar and butter together in mixer on medium speed until smooth. Add eggs, vanilla and canned milk.
Add flour mixture until mixed good.
You can separate dough into 2 parts and roll like log into wax paper.
Chill and cut.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crab fondue dip
directions: In saucepan, heat cream cheese until soft. Add all other ingredients (except bread) and heat thoroughly. Arrange chunks of bread on baking sheet and bake until crispy. When mixture is heated, put into fondue pan (works best if it stays warm) and use the bread chunks to dip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Do not add salt.
Drain broccoli and chop up.
In mixing bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise, onion, egg, Cheddar cheese, Season-All and milk.
Stir in broccoli.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Mix well. Serve over romaine lettuce and croutons.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine ingredients; bring to a boil and let boil 3 minutes. Remove and pour in baked pie shell and let cool; top with Cool Whip.

title: proteena-noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine mushroom soup, milk, salt and poultry seasoning and heat.
Blend cheeses and beat well; add olives, onion, pepper and parsley.
Blend well.
Place half the noodles in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with half the cheese mixture, half the Proteena and half the soup.
Repeat layers.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Garnish with pimiento.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: oklahoma coconut cake
directions: Cook a regular size sheet cake from a box of yellow cake mix. You may leave cake in the pan.
Using a wooden spoon handle, make holes all over the cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut over the entire cake.
Spread Cool Whip on cake and sprinkle with coconut.
Place cherries on top of cake and keep refrigerated.
Delicious!

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients lightly.
Reserve 1/2 cup noodles for topping.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with noodles; bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, shortening and pumpkin.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Lightly grease and flour jelly pan.
Add dry mixture to pumpkin mixture.
Put in 11 x 17-inch jelly pan; bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix this together well.
Bake in 4-quart casserole.
Cover meat loaf with ketchup topping.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mandarin fluff
directions: Place oranges in a bowl. Fold in the cool whip. Just before serving fold in pecans.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: In a wok or large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Add garlic and cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Stir in green cabbage, red cabbage, carrots, onion, bell peppers, soy sauce and ginger. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 10 minutes. In a small bowl, combine water and cornstarch. Mix well. Add cornstarch mixture to wok, stirring until sauce thickens, about 1 minute. Serve immediately.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, chipped ham and beef together.
Add diced green onions.
Shape into ball and refrigerate.
Wallah!

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Combine dissolved bouillon cubes, soy sauce and cornstarch. Brown the beef and onion in a large skillet; break beef apart to a crumbly mixture and brown thoroughly.
Add the water chestnuts (with juice), the broccoli and carrots.
Pour the bouillon, soy sauce and cornstarch mixture over all.
Bring to a slight boil, then lower heat and let simmer until vegetables are tender (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Stir occasionally while cooking.
Serve over cooked rice and add soy sauce to taste.
Makes about 4 generous servings.

title: trab's favorite gravy(by goody)
directions: Melt Crisco in skillet over medium heat. Add flour.
Stir until dark brown.
Add water.
Cook until desired thickness.

title: almond roca
directions: Mix sugar, butter and water in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook on high heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Reduce to medium-high heat and cook until tan, 276° (285° sea level).

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Using a 32-cup coffee pot, place sugar, salt, cloves and cinnamon in the basket.
Pour juices and water into pot and perk until hot.

title: wet bottom shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, shortening and flour.
Save 1/2 cup of mixture.
Bring water to boil.
Add baking soda.
Stir in molasses.
Add beaten egg.
Mix together, then add crumbs and liquid together.
Pour into pie crust and top with remaining 1/2 cup crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: marie's pizza
directions: Mix dough ingredients and knead enough to make a workable dough. Grease 2 large baking sheets and 2 small ones. Divide the dough between them. Greasing your hands enables you to spread dough out easier over each baking sheet.

title: miss maten's meringue
directions: Boil the sugar, cornstarch and water.
Make a thick paste. Let cool. Take the egg whites and whip until peaked. Add paste and beat until foamy. Gradually add the sugar and pinch of salt (vanilla flavoring is optional).
Seal meringue to crust and bake at 325° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: holiday fruitcake
directions: Grease and flour 10 to 12-cup Bundt pan.
In large bowl, combine eggs and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
By hand, stir until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 80 to 90 minutes until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool 15 minutes inverted on cooling rack.
Cool completely.
To store, wrap tightly in foil or plastic wrap.
Store in refrigerator.
This freezes well also.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Pour milk on crumbs and let stand.
Butter baking dish and put in macaroni; add remaining ingredients to milk mixture and pour over macaroni.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: green beans and broccoli
directions: Fry the salt pork until it is crisp.
Add the onion, green pepper and celery and cook until the mixture is pulpy.
Add tomato paste and cook until most of the liquid in the pan has evaporated. Add the drained pigeon peas, thyme, salt and pepper and cook for a further 2 minutes.
Pour in the rice and add water to cover. Cover the pot tightly and allow the mixture to simmer until all the liquid has evaporated.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Put all dry ingredients into large bowl.
Mix hot water with molasses.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Add shortening and egg. Stir with spoon until blended.
Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles following package directions; drain.
Cook hamburger.
Add oregano to spaghetti sauce.
In greased 3-quart baking dish, make layers in order.
Use 1/2 spaghetti sauce, layer of noodles, hamburger, cottage cheese, rest of spaghetti sauce, another layer of noodles, then sliced Mozzarella cheese.

title: turkey salad
directions: Cook turkey breast, after wrapping in foil, adding salt and basting with margarine.
Continue to baste as turkey bakes.
Cool turkey and chop.
Add salad dressing, pickle relish, boiled eggs and diced celery.

title: pineapple sherbet salad
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple;
add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Heat
to
boiling;
add
gelatin
and stir until dissolved.	Stir
in sherbet and cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, add peeled diced banana, almonds and pineapple. Chill until firm. Serve on salad greens. Yields 6 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Mix ginger ale, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Just before serving, pour in choice of pop and ice cream.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Prepare jello and boiling water, let cool.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip Pet milk until it looks like whipped cream.
The milk must be very cold to whip.
Put it in the refrigerator overnight before whipping.
Add jello mixture to the cream cheese mixture and then add it all together to the whipped milk.
Use large pan for the crust and keep refrigerated.
Reserve some of the cracker mixture to sprinkle on top.

title: banana bread
directions: In a bowl, mix together dry ingredients.
Set aside.
In a second bowl, beat eggs slightly. Beat in crushed bananas and melted butter or margarine.
Add flour mixture and stir just enough to combine.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into a buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 55 minutes.

title: clam stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and mince finely.
Combine butter and garlic in small saucepan and heat slowly until butter is melted, stirring occasionally.
Coat mushroom caps with mixture.
Set on baking sheet.
Preheat broiler.
Combine clam juice and minced mushroom stems in small saucepan over medium heat and cook until tender.
Add clams, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper; heat. Divide evenly among caps.
Broil 6 inches from heat until lightly golden and heated through, about 5 to 8 minutes.

title: caramel ice cream balls(makes 36 or more servings)
directions: Melt
oleo.
Mix nuts, sugar, flour and oatmeal together. Pour
oleo	over
mixture and mix well.
Put in a 3-quart Pyrex dish
x
15-inches).
Pat down well.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown.
Cool completely, then break into crumbs.

title: pasta with marinara sauce and ricotta
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over pasta.
Stir in Ricotta cheese.
You may substitute 1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella for the Ricotta cheese.

title: divinity
directions: Dissolve sugar, syrup and salt in hot water.
Cook, without stirring, to 248° or to boil stage.
Wash down any crystals that may form on the sides of the pan during cooking.
Remove from heat and pour slowly over the stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly with a wire whisk.
Add vanilla and continue beating until mixture will hold its shape when dropped from a spoon.
Drop by spoonfuls or spread on a buttered pan and mark squares.
Very good when dipped in chocolate!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except the pecans.
The next day, roll ball in pecans.

title: vienna pinwheels
directions: Mix flour, salt, butter and cream cheese together, as for pie crust, by cutting in shortening with a fork.
Roll out paper thin on a floured board.
Blend liverwurst and lemon juice.
Spread mixture onto rolled pastry.
Roll up dough as for jelly roll; wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Cut into thin slices.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Cut bread into the size you would like your croutons to be. Place cut bread into a large bowl.
Melt butter and pour over them and toss to coat.
Then add your salad dressing mix.
Toss to coat. Place bread on a cookie sheet, and bake slowly at 200 degrees for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: rosh hashanah honey cake(pareve)
directions: Combine oil, sugar, honey, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Mix well (2 minutes on electric mixer).
Set aside. Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and cloves.
Set aside.
Grease 10-inch Bundt pan and flour lightly. Add flour mixture to egg mixture alternately with coffee.
Mix well (2 minutes).
Add nuts.
Fill Bundt or 4 to 5 very small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender.
Drain water and cover potatoes with milk.
Fry bacon until crisp and saute onion until tender.
Crumble bacon into soup and add onion.
Add cheese 20 minutes before serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cut chipped ham in small pieces and brown slightly.
Add chili sauce and ginger ale or Seven-Up.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water; add fruit and marshmallows.
Let set in refrigerator until set.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together: sugar, cream cheese and smooth peanut butter. Fold in Cool Whip.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add when lukewarm.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts and chill.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in 9 x 13-inch pan and slide into oven to melt.
Remove pan from oven; tip to spread butter and sprinkle evenly with graham cracker crumbs.
Top with coconut, then chocolate pieces, then butterscotch pieces.
Drizzle condensed milk over all and then sprinkle with nuts.
Press nuts lightly into the mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut in small bars.

title: buffet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Heat until cheese is melted and all ingredients are mixed together.
Pour over potatoes and blend.
Pour the mixed ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until bubbly.
Use as a side dish or add ham for a main dish.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all and refrigerate.

title: shoya chicken(for 6 to 10 people)
directions: Cut chicken into pieces (roughly 2 to 3 pieces per breast half). Dip each piece into beaten egg and then into flour two times.
Fry in deep fat fryer or wok, approximately 20 minutes. Fry several pieces at one time.
Set aside in a large container with a tight lid.

title: banana split pies
directions: Beat the following with mixer exactly 15 minutes:
eggs, margarine and powdered sugar.
Spread over crust.
Spread drained pineapple, then sliced bananas over filling.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts and cut up cherries.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip and stir well.
Add fruit cocktail and stir until all is mixed together. Refrigerate until set or ready to eat.
Sets in about 1/2 hour.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Slice uncooked sweet potatoes thin and crosswise.
Drop slices into hot grease and fry until browned.
Sprinkle with salt, sugar or cinnamon.
Leftover baked sweet potatoes can be sliced into 1-inch thick slices and pan fried in butter or bacon drippings. Sprinkle with cinnamon or sugar.

title: cheese buds
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In mixer, blend flour, butter, cheese and seasonings.
Pinch off small, half dollar-sized pieces and place on a cookie sheet.
Top with pecan halves.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool and eat.

title: nana's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine, sugar and salt together with mixer.
Next, add eggs.
Beat well until beaten together.
Add flavoring and beat.
Add flour in increments, beating each time.
(Should be fairly thick and hard to mix.) Then add milk and beat.
Pour into Pam-sprayed tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Great! (like all my Nana's cooking).

title: lamb parmesan
directions: Make lamb into patties and fry, drain.
Place patties in baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese begins to turn and bubble.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Pour 1/4 cup chicken broth in bottom of casserole bowl.
Cook onions with 2 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Melt cheese.
Then mix soups, tomatoes, onions, and cheese.
Layer half of chicken, then sprinkle half of crumbled
Doritos on top of chicken.
Then spread half of mixture on top of Doritos.
Repeat layering with the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese melts.
After baking, sprinkle some Doritos on top.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind peppers, pears and onions in food chopper.
Add sugar, salt, vinegar and allspice.
Boil for 30 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: english toffee(may prepare ahead.  makes one 10 x 13-inch slab.)
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, cracker crumbs, sugar, vanilla and nuts; blend well.
Hand roll into little finger-size logs.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
With fork, dip logs, one at a time, into chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper to harden chocolate.

title: pear and swiss cheese salad
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Add pears, cheese and cashews.
Toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates.
Serves 4.

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Slice tortillas in strips.
Combine soups, broth, sour cream, onions and chilies.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, layer tortillas, half the chicken, half the sauce and half the cheese.
Repeat. Bake, covered, at 350° for about 45 minutes, then uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: flying saucers
directions: Empty ice cream into a bowl.
With a spoon, stir ice cream until it softens just a little.
With a butter knife, spread softened ice cream on a cookie.
Cover it quickly with another cookie.
Wrap the ice cream sandwich in a square of aluminum foil, and pop into freezer.
Use the rest of ice cream and cookies to make more sandwiches working quickly so ice cream won't melt. Freeze for 24 hours.

title: curly noodle salad
directions: Mix all of the vegetables and noodles thoroughly.
Add the bottle of Zesty Italian dressing and mix well until everything is thoroughly coated and place in the refrigerator overnight.
Ready to serve as is.

title: cheese and bacon strata
directions: Butter a loaf-size casserole.
Place 2 slices of bread on bottom.
Add grated onion.
Over onion, put 1 cup of the grated cheese and the crumbled bacon.
Top with 2 or 3 more slices of bread to cover completely.
Beat the eggs.
Add the milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over the other ingredients.
Top with the remaining 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Set in a pan of hot water and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter together.
Add sugar and beat for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add vanilla and flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato and cabbage soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add the water, cabbage, potatoes, bouillon, pepper and garlic.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in ham; heat through.
Yield: 12 to 14 servings (about 3 1/2 quarts).

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, parsley, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup condensed tomato soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape in about 15 to 20 small meat balls.
Place in skillet.
Brown lightly.
Place drained meatballs in casserole dish and mix remaining soup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough to 2 long triangles.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press on bottom and 1/2 inch up sides. Seal perforations.

title: bacon-stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: *They won't roll on the platter if you scoop out the bottoms and stand them stem side down.

title: baked bean bonanza
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: salmon or tuna loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in greased pan at 350 degrees about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add flour and milk; stir constantly.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into baking dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms(seashore crab)
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove and chop stems.
Place stems in small bowl with onion or butter, if included in recipe.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Arrange caps on paper towel lined plate with larger caps to outside.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, until heated, rotating plate once or twice.
Microwave at High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mound in mushroom caps.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook roast in a little water in bottom of roaster until it falls apart.
In a saucepan, combine ketchup, meat stock, sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Chop up meat and cook together for 2 hours on low flame.

title: praline peach cobbler
directions: In a saucepan, mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and water.
Stir until smooth.
Add peaches. Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Set aside.
In a bowl, combine flour and remaining sugar. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk and stir just until moistened.
If needed, add additional buttermilk, one tablespoon at a time, until dough clings together. Turn onto a floured surface.
Knead gently 6 to 8 times.

Roll into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle. Combine butter, brown sugar and pecans. Spread over the dough to within 1/2-inch of the edges. Starting with long sides, roll up jelly roll fashion. Cut into 12 pieces 1-inch each.
Place on top of the peach mixture. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 servings.

title: goodie bars
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars and roll in powdered sugar.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Sift together
flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add milk and beat
until well blended.	Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly
until	mixture
boils and thickens.
Cook one minute; remove
from
heat; add butter and vanilla.
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Spread rhubarb in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb and dot with butter.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fruity ginger ale mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool to room temperature.
Slowly add ginger ale.
Arrange apple wedges and some pineapple in a 4 1/2-cup mold.
Pour in 3/4 cup of the lemon gelatin mixture.
Chill until almost firm.

title: apple spice custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix.
Stir in apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until done.
In medium bowl, combine milk, sour cream and lemon juice.
Remove cake; spread cream mixture on top.
Return to oven. Bake 10 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cool and refrigerate leftovers.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash broccoli and chop or break into florets.
Place in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle with cheese. Mix balance of ingredients and pour into broccoli and cheese. Bake in preheated oven about 45 minutes or until custard tests done.
Serve in wedges.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Mix butter and sugar thoroughly.
Work in flour by hand and chill.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll 1/3 to 1/2-inch thick. Cut into squares or oblongs.
(I prefer to make into a pie shape and cut it into pie slices.)
Place on ungreased baking sheet.*
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
(The tops do not brown during baking.)
Makes 2 dozen (1 1/2 x 1-inch) cookies.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt the butter and add the sugar, cocoa, eggs, vanilla, flour, walnuts and salt.
Cook at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top.
Let stand 5 minutes, then frost.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add water and oil.
Mix well. It will be sticky.
Let rest 10 minutes.

title: quick zucchini patties
directions: Mix in order listed and fry like potato cakes.
Serves 6.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend.
In separate bowl, mix flour, powdered cocoa, soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
(Stir in nuts if desired.)

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and water in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir to dissolve Jell-O.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit; set aside.
Combine milk and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in Jell-O mixture and add nuts.
Pour into a 9-cup mold and chill.
Serves 20.

title: burritos
directions: Brown pork (drain and add tomato sauce and onions).
Season and cook until meat absorbs the sauce. Fry tortillas and put 1 big tablespoon of meat and one of beans on each tortilla serve with salad.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk, blend well and add dry ingredients.
Stir together. Add zucchini.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Does not need frosting.

title: shrimp and artichoke hearts casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt 4 1/2 tablespoons of butter.
With whisk, stir in flour until blended.
Gradually beat in milk and cream; cook until thick and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper; set aside.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash and cut up chicken.
Sprinkle seasoned salt, pepper, celery, onions and bell peppers over chicken.
Add water.
Cover and bake in oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Set oven at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk and pudding together as directed on box.
Pour into pie crusts and let thicken in refrigerator.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pies.
May garnish with chocolate chips if you want too.

title: slum gulley
directions: Chop onion and brown in pan with oil or butter.
Peel potatoes and slice.
Cut sausages in pieces.
Make a layer of meat, layer of potatoes, layer of corn and part of onions.
Build up until you have used all of ingredients.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at moderate temperature until cooked in covered dish, about 1 hour.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza skillet supper combo
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef, onions and bell pepper; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce and soup; blend well.
Stir in water and pepperoni.
Bring to boil; stir in uncooked noodles.
Cover; cook over medium heat, 10 to 15 minutes or until pasta is tender, stirring frequently.
Uncover; cook an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until sauce is of desired consistency.
Remove from heat; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: orange sauce
directions: Heat half of orange juice and syrup over low flame.
Dissolve cornstarch in remaining orange juice.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes after bringing to full boil.
Serve hot or cold over pancakes or waffles.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at one time.
Do not use a mixer, use a spoon.
Bake at 350° in a flat pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: low-fat lemon chicken
directions: Cook chicken, onion, carrot and garlic in heated butter in skillet until chicken is lightly browned (about 5 minutes). Combine cornstarch and broth; add lemon juice, peel, salt and rice. Mix and add to skillet.
Reduce heat; add broccoli and parsley. Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 4 servings containing 367 calories per serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake in greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll each slice or 2 (peeling left on is optional) in crescent roll. Melt butter in dish and coat each side with butter. Mix sugar and orange juice together. Pour over apples. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split freeze
directions: Whip cream, slice bananas thinly.
Drain cherries and chop nuts.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a freezable container.
Cover with aluminum foil and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: quick green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and soup together.
Put onions on top.
Bake in oven until onions on top are brown and crispy at 450°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in a large pot.
Add chicken and brown well.
Add cubes, garlic and celery powder.
Next add rice and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Cover with lid and turn down on low.
Cook for approximately 30 minutes on low.
Serve while hot.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all together in electric frying pan except baking soda. Cook 10 minutes at 350°.
Add baking soda; mix well.

title: homemade banana layer cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans; set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° until it bubbles (approximately 30 minutes).

title: cream pies
directions: Scald milk and cream.
Combine flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Mix together thoroughly.
Add to scalded milk and cook until thick and smooth.
Stir a small amount of mixture into mixture and cook a few minutes longer.
Add vanilla.
Top with meringue.
(I also make in microwave using 5 minutes on High, then 2 or 3 minutes at a time until done.)
(Use one baked pie crust.)

title: olive cheese snacks
directions: Blend bacon-cheese spread with butter until light and fluffy. Add Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Stir in flour and mix to form a dough.
Shape around olives, using about 1 teaspoon of dough for each olive.
Place in ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheese) well.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Microwave 3 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in sm. saucepan, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook to hard ball (252°) stirring occasionally.
Combine egg whites and gelatin, beat until mixture forms peaks.
Pour hot syrup into egg whites, beating until candy looses gloss and holds shape, add coconut and pecans, if desired.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: haley pena eggs
directions: Place chips on cookie sheet.
Place jalapeno slice in center of each chip.
Place a round slice of Monterey Jack cheese on top. Then center a smaller round Cheddar slice on top.
Put under broiler until cheese melts.

title: sweet potato crumble
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, margarine, milk and vanilla. Put in baking dish. Combine brown sugar, pecans, flour and margarine. Crumble over sweet potatoes mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: new orleans style gumbo
directions: Place chicken, sausage, tomatoes, and okra in just enough water to cover chicken and cook until done.
Take chicken out of broth and pull meat off of bone.
Put chicken back in broth with all seasonings and shrimp.
Mix cajun gumbo mix as directed.
Pour in the pot with other ingredients and cook until shrimp are done. Serve over rice.

title: shoe peg casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and put on top.
Dot with margarine (about 1 stick).
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove stems from mushroom caps; dash, chop and cook stems in 1 tablespoon butter until moisture evaporates.
Combine the cooked stems with all the remaining ingredients, except the mushroom caps; set aside.
Wash the mushroom caps, drain and pat dry.
Stuff the caps with filling; arrange on baking dish.
Add a little water to bottom of pan to prevent sticking.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° and serve hot.

title: "bring your beans" 4-bean bake
directions: Fry bacon until crispy. Remove from pan. Fry onions in bacon grease.
Mix all remaining ingredients in large casserole dish, adding bacon and onions. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating well.
Stir in extracts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Yields 1 (10-inch) tube cake.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and pepper.
Add a touch of Worcestershire.
Add onions and continue browning.
Add olives and pepper.
Boil water while preparing meat, then add noodles and cook for 8 minutes.
Add pimento, corn, tomato soup and tomato sauce.
Put in casserole dish.
Place cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut pecan squares
directions: Cream the butter with the brown sugar.
Add 1 c. flour and mix well.
Press into greased 8 x 8 x 2 in. pan, spreading batter evenly into the corners.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°F for 20 min.
Meanwhile, beat the eggs until frothy, gradually adding the light brown sugar, and beating until thick.
Add pecans and coconut which have been tossed with the remaining flour.
Flavor with vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Spread over baked crust and bake for 20 min. more in moderate oven until well browned. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool and cut into 1 in. squares.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions on box.
Let cool 15 minutes; then poke holes down through cake with utility fork. Mix milk, sugar and half of coconut in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Spoon over cake; let cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip and half of the remaining coconut together and spread over cake.
Top with remaining coconut; keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli casserole(great for picnics or get togethers)
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add broccoli and stir.
Add soup, cooked rice and cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake uncovered in oven 30 minutes at 350°.

title: white salad
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk together on low heat, stirring constantly.
Beat well.
Stir in cream cheese until melted.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple; fold in cherry halves and mandarin oranges, then fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Fill with water (about 6 cups), until it looks like soup.
Can be done in crock-pot all day at high setting or in pot on stove at medium heat for 3 hours.
Cut up beef into bite-size pieces at end. Add water at end to bring to proper "soup consistency."

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except onion soup and chicken.
Place in a greased 8 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of onion soup over rice.
Place chicken on top and cover with remaining soup mix. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not add salt or any other liquids.

title: molasses cream cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or more.
Roll out on floured board and cut into favorite shapes or roll in hand to the size of a walnut.
Then roll in white sugar and press down with glass.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
May frost when cooled. Makes 8 dozen soft cookies.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix last 2 ingredients together in a large shallow bowl or plate.
Cream together 1 1/2 cups sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and blend well.
In a separate bowl mix flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls and roll in the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Fry bacon and remove from drippings.
Saute onion in drippings.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer on top of stove for 40 minutes.

title: creamy corn chowder
directions: Cut bacon into 1/2-inch dices; set aside.
Peel onion and cut into slices (thin).
Cut peeled potatoes into 1/2-inch dices. Cook bacon over moderate heat until golden brown and bacon is crisp.
Add potatoes and water; bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add cream-style corn (undrained) to potato mixture.
Stir in milk, butter, salt, sugar and pepper. Cover pan; simmer 5 minutes or until hot.
When ready to serve, sprinkle chowder with parsley.
Eat with cheese biscuits.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Whisk all ingredients together or place in blender until completely mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
The center will be soft after baking but will set up when cooled.
Refrigerate.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a large Dutch oven; saute green pepper and onion until peppers are crisp-tender.
Stir in the chicken, mushrooms, pimento, soup, milk, garlic powder and salt.
Drain spaghetti and add to mixture; toss.
