Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Sprinkle with cheese; bake 10 minutes longer or until the cheese is melted.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Grease three 8-inch cake pans.
Set oven to 375°.
Cream the butter and sugar well; add egg yolks.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk, then add vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ground beef and gravy
directions: Make out ground beef patties.
Put in frying pan and cover. Cook on low-medium heat. Slice onion.
Put on top of patties and simmer.
Make gravy according to package directions.
When patties are done, pour gravy over top and let set for 5 minutes.

title: lisa's chicken
directions: Arrange chipped beef on bottom of baking dish.
Wrap 1/2 strip of bacon around each chicken piece.
Place chicken on top of chipped beef.

title: bohemian kolacky(servings:  4)
directions: Cut butter into flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add yolks and sweet cream.
Shape into ball and chill overnight.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cutter or shape into rounds or squares. Place fruit filling in center.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Place on tomato slice.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan. While still warm, poke holes in cake and pour on caramel topping and Eagle Brand condensed milk.
Chill.
Spread with Cool Whip and top with broken candy bars and/or chopped pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheesy biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in oleo, add milk and 3/4 cup cheese.
Stir.

title: rolls
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add egg.
Crumble in yeast and salt.
Make dough with water and flour.
Place in refrigerator.
Let rise 1 hour before baking.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: pink witch
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together in blender or large mixing bowl.
Add ginger ale, blending slowly.
Serve cold.
Serves 20 (1/2 cups).

title: low calorie soup
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Lower heat; simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Good served with corn bread!

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: In large roasting pan or stock pot, put water, chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook about one hour on low heat until chicken is done. Remove chicken and dice.
Add back to water stock chicken, chopped onion, carrots, celery and bouillon cubes.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours. Add noodles to desired thickness, and Swanson chicken soup.
Cook until done 30 to 45 minutes on low heat.

title: peach dessert
directions: Grease 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
Pour peaches in, then pour the juice in.
Cover with cake mix.
Pour melted butter over the top. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: creamy potato leek soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine leeks, potatoes, chicken broth and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Puree mixture in a blender or food processor. Return to saucepan.
Stir in sour cream using a wire whisk, add milk (and optional chives).
Heat gently, making sure not to burn the bottom of the soup.
Makes 8 1/2 cups.

title: tea cakes(maw maw kelly's)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Roll part at a time very thin.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: orange cheese salad
directions: Put jello, marshmallows and cream cheese in bowl and pour 1 pint boiling
water over; beat with
mixer
until
smooth.
Let cool
until thickened.
Add whipped cream,
sugar,
nuts
and pineapple.
Pour into serving dish and when well set up,
pour small box of orange jello over top.
Let jello cool before pouring on.
Scatter nuts over top.

title: rouladen
directions: You will also need some string.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Toss to mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle paprika on top; chill, covered, for hours. Serves 8.

title: mexican dip
directions: This dip is in five layers. In about 12-inches round, about the size of a pizza pan, layer.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Mix sugar, flour, pineapple juice, egg and butter in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring until smooth and thickened, 10 to 15 minutes; use a whisk for best results.
Cool completely.
Fold in whipped cream; chill at least 3 hours.
Serve with fresh fruit; apples, pears, strawberries, etc.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, seasoning and pepper.
Roll into ball.
Roll in ground nuts.

title: freezer cabbage slaw
directions: Sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt over cabbage and let stand 1 hour; drain.
Dice and add celery, green pepper, onion and carrots.
Mix sugar, water, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed in saucepan and bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Pour mixture over cabbage.
Mix and freeze.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Saute onions in 2 to 3 tablespoons of artichoke marinade, until soft.
Mix Worcestershire, Tabasco and eggs.
Fold sauteed onions, cheese and chopped artichoke hearts into the egg mixture and spread into a square buttered baking pan.
Melt butter in a saucepan and fold in bread crumbs; mix thoroughly.
Spread bread crumbs over top of artichoke mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, or until mixture is set.
Remove and cool enough to put in refrigerator.
Allow to refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Garnish with parsley.
Cut into 1-inch squares to serve. Stores well in refrigerator overnight.

title: pie melon pie
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch uncooked pie crusts.
Cook 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Cook an additional 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chili rubbed chicken
directions: Preheat grill or large cast-iron skillet over medium heat. Pat chicken dry with paper towel. Rub chicken with garlic, then sprinkle with chili powder.
Cook 3 minutes each side.

title: orange salad
directions: Prepare orange jello, hot water and sherbet; let cool until it begins to set (only a few minutes), then add mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.

title: chicken tortilla wraps
directions: Marinate chicken in lime juice, garlic, salt, pepper, chili powder and oil. Spread on tortillas cream cheese, cumin, mashed black beans, salsa and lettuce.
Cook chicken on grill and slice into thin strips. Add chicken to tortillas, roll and/or slice. Enjoy!

title: layered chili
directions: Chop pepper and onion.
You can use regular kidney beans. Precook and save 1 1/2 cups of the liquid.
Cook onions and pepper in oil until tender.
Add mustard seed; cook 1 minute and add rest of the ingredients with liquid from can of tomatoes and beans. Stir, breaking up tomatoes with spoon.
Simmer rapidly, uncovered, for about 40 minutes, until most of the liquid is cooked away. Top with cucumber, grated cheese or chilies if you like it hot.

title: bird's nest
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over low heat.
Add peanuts or peanut butter, salt and chow mein noodles.
Stir.
Drop on wax paper.

title: pretzel joy
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt chocolate.
Pour over mixture of dry ingredients.
Stir until coated.
Spread on 15 x 11-inch cookie sheet covered with waxed paper.
Let harden and break into pieces.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes in 8 x 11-inch pan.

title: beaten biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450° to 475°.
Sift flour with soda and salt. Rub lard in thoroughly until it looks leathery.
Add water and mix.
Use rolling pin to flatten dough about 3/4-inch thick and cut out.
Bake 15 minutes in a thick black pan.
This recipe was taken from a very old cookbook.

title: dad's favorite casserole
directions: Cook noodles until barely tender.
Drain and rinse.
In large skillet, saute onion in butter until light yellow.
Set aside. In same skillet, cook ground beef, stirring to break into bits until it changes color.
Add onion and cottage cheese.
Gently stir to blend.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Set aside to cool.
Prepare other ingredients.
Mix all.
Pour Zesty Italian salad dressing over salad. Toss and serve.
Makes a lot!

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and oil to liquid. Mix with flour.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, soup, butter and onion.
Cook on low heat until done.
Add Cheez Whiz and cooked rice.
Layer chicken and broccoli.
Mix in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix together the cake mix and 2 eggs. Press the mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs, confectioners sugar and melted margarine.
Pour over cake mix in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown. Cut into squares.

title: potatoes with rosemary and cheese
directions: Place potatoes in a shallow 1 1/2-quart dish; sprinkle with the oil and seasonings.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring twice until potatoes are almost tender.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let stand 5 minutes until potatoes are tender and cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: classic lasagne
directions: Lightly brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes (put through blender), paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagne; drain.

title: country corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add beaten egg and buttermilk to make batter stiff.
Add slightly cooled shortening and beat until well mixed.
Bake at 425° in greased pan for 15 minutes. Then brush top with margarine and bake 10 more minutes.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Mix Jell-O, pudding mix and water together.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly, unless cooked in the microwave.
Put in a covered container to cool and thicken.
Add Cool Whip and mandarin orange pieces, using some to garnish top.

title: cornish hens
directions: Split birds in half and sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place each half on square of heavy foil.
Pour olive oil over each and grease well.
Place birds skin side down and fill cavity with other ingredients mixed together.
Fold foil squares around birds to keep in all juices.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour or until tender.
Open foil and turn birds skin side up. Raise heat and brown about 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Crumble and drain.
Layer bread, eggs, onions, sausage, and cheese alternately in a greased 9 x 13 baking dish until all ingredients are used.
Pour milk over top to moisten and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: marinade for teriyaki
directions: Mix all ingredients except meat in a bowl and stir until the sugar is dissolved.
Pour mixture over the meat and marinate 12 to 24 hours in the refrigerator.
Bake on a broiler pan at 350° or grill on barbecue.
Baste meat throughout the cooking time.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff. Add the sugar, baking powder, vanilla, crumbs and pecans.
Pour into a lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except topping in a mixing bowl and mix well. Pour into a 2 qt. casserole dish. Sprinkle topping mixture over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift dry ingredients on wax paper.
Melt oleo.
Beat in sugar, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture from wax paper.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
While it is warm, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix first four items together and set aside.
Mix rest and add to first batch.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or longer, if needed.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Break off broccoli florets.
Dice cucumber.
Combine all ingredients except tomato and several onion rings.
Marinate in fridge several hours or overnight.
To serve, add tomato and garnish with onion rings.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tortillas
directions: Roll out.
Cook in skillet or on top of stove.

title: spinach pizza
directions: Layer ingredients in order on crust.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 22 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar, salt and Karo.
Bring to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add soda and mix well.
Put popcorn and nuts in a large roasting pan.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn and stir to cover all popcorn and nuts.
Place mixture in preheated 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Pour mixture onto wax paper to cool.
Break into bite-size pieces. Store in an airtight container.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal, raisins and water.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
In another bowl, beat egg.
Stir in milk, oil and remaining ingredients.
Add cereal mixture (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin lined tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: german hash
directions: Mix all together.
Cook until vegetables are soft.
Add water if needed.
Thicken with butter or cornstarch or flour mixture with cool water.
Serve with toast, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: marinated sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fry the sausage in small balls. Drain. Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over the cooked sausage balls.
Let stand overnight; serve warm.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Beat eggs well. Dip pork chops in eggs, then dip in corn flakes. Place chops in nonstick pan. Bake at 350° or until tender.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out all water.
Mix all ingredients. Make into balls.
Freeze.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mama's cornbread for dressing
directions: Place meal in a bowl; add eggs, milk and flour.
Stir.
Add hot Crisco oil and stir until well blended.
Place this mixture in a pan and bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until browned.
(This makes 3 pans of cornbread.)

title: endive salad with potatoes
directions: In a salad bowl, combine endive and potatoes. In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine the remaining ingredients; shake well. Drizzle over salad; toss to coat. Serve immediately.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk.
Put in double boiler. After milk becomes hot, add beaten egg yolks. When thick, add vanilla and oleo.
Pour in baked shell. Beat egg whites for meringue.
Brown in a 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: pork chops cacciatore
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in 11x7x1-1/2-inch baking pan.
Top each chop with a thin onion slice.

title: herb chicken
directions: Mix ingredients.
Dip in chicken breasts and then roll in herb dressing.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours in a 350° oven.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, onion, soup and sour cream in bowl and add 1/2 of cheese, mix well and spread in greased 9x13 pan.
Top with remainder of cheese and all of the onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until gold and bubbly.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Mix
together all ingredients and marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: black walnut sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder, milk, flavoring and sour cream.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix tomato soup and cream of mushroom soup together.
Put in bottom of an 8 x 11 1/2-inch ungreased baking dish.
Brown ground beef and onion lightly on medium heat.
Drain and spread over soup.
Precook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and place over ground beef.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover baking dish with its top or aluminum foil. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube or 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool.
Invert on serving plate.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook rice according to package directions.

title: fast scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn in saucepan; add crumbled crackers and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Can put crushed crackers on top for garnish.

title: vamino bars
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients until well blended; boil over low heat, stirring for 2 minutes. Add the graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pat down and cool.
Combine the 1/4 cup butter, milk, pudding and confectioners sugar.
Mix thoroughly with mixer and spread over bottom layer. Melt the chocolate and 2 tablespoons butter. Spread on top of creamy layer.
Refrigerate until set. Cut into squares.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook Ro-Tel and soups in pan until hot (not boiling).
Using a 2-quart casserole dish or a roasting pan, layer chicken, Doritos, onions and part of the soup mixture.
Continue layering and then pour remainder of the soup mixture on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with shredded cheese and place in oven long enough for cheese to melt.

title: barbecue sauce and ribs
directions: Cook sauce for 10 minutes.
Brown ribs; pour sauce over ribs. Bake in covered pan at 375° for 2 hours.
Turn down oven to 275° and bake without cover for last 1/2 hour.

title: chuck roast
directions: Shake flour in bag, add sauce, wine, water, bouillon, salt and pepper in bag.
Add roast, mushrooms and vegetables.
Turn several times to coat.
Tie bag.
Make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: almost mrs. fields
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugars well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oats, salt, baking powder and soda.
Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and grated chocolate.

title: chatterbox salad dressing
directions: Put everything into a bowl and beat with a fork or eggbeater until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together, leaving part of the cheese for top of the casserole.
Put in baking dish. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Cut corn from cob, scraping the cob.
Add milk and flour to eggs. Beat until fairly smooth. Add corn and butter; mix well. Spoon into pan of medium-hot oil. Brown on both sides. Freeze leftovers for reheating.

title: sweet-sour beef balls with pineapple and peppers
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, salt, pepper and onion (chopped).
Form into 18 balls or more.
Brown them in a small amount of oil; drain.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes until brown.

title: home made brown bread
directions: In a stainless steel bowl pour boiling water over raisins and baking soda.
Then add butter and cool.

title: potato soup
directions: In large soup pot, add potatoes, broth, water, salt, pepper, garlic, onion, carrots and celery.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Add ham, milk and cheese. Continue to simmer approximately 10 minutes. More salt, pepper or garlic may be added to taste.

title: cold rice salad
directions: Cook rice in broth until tender.
Mix oil, vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper, dill and basil.
Toss with hot rice.
Refrigerate, covered, 1 hour or more.
Before serving, mix remaining ingredients and toss.

title: rolled round steak and dressing
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook stuffing according to package.
Lay round steak flat.
Spread dressing over steak.
Roll steak up with dressing inside.
Tie steak.
Place in dish and pour soup over steak.
Bake uncovered 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon butter
directions: To prepare lemon butter, beat eggs until light.
Add sugar with lemon juice and grated lemon peel.
Combine in a saucepan with butter.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened to a pudding, constantly stirring.
Let cool and spread on cake. Serves 8.

title: french vanilla cappuccino
directions: In a large bowl, combine the above ingredients and stir until the mixture is well blended.
Place mix in a wide mouth quart canning jar.
You can attach a gift tag with the serving directions on how to prepare the cappuccino and
place a fabric top on it to make it more attractive.

title: cookies from a cake mix
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine dry cake mix, oil and eggs in bowl and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: whole wheat gingerbread cookies
directions: Beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and egg; blend well.
Stir in all-purpose flour and wheat flour, baking soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Mix well.
If necessary, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for easier handling.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll out and cut on lightly floured surface.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 9 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool completely before decorating.

title: cheese and pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Pour melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: gormet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with
skins
on.
Skin potatoes and cube or shred. Mix other
ingredients and stir through potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening or oleo.
Add brown sugar.
Mix well and cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, pecans and chocolate chips. Grease oblong pan.
Add batter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Pour apple cider and ginger ale into a percolator.
Put red hots, cloves and cinnamon sticks into percolator filter. Percolate mixture until done.
Will keep in the refrigerator for several days.

title: sunshine pound cake
directions: Sift flour.
Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add extracts; sprinkle baking powder on top.
Beat at medium speed for 8 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Place in a cool oven.
Turn on 300° and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut meat in cubes.
Brown meat and onions in oil.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Add	water
and
stir until slightly thickened.	Add bouillon cubes and wine.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.	Serves 6.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: In a bowl mash potato and egg yolks.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, relish and onion, mix well.
Then, using teaspoon, put about 1 heaping teaspoonful of mixture to each egg white.
Sprinkle tray of eggs with paprika and refrigerate before serving or serve immediately.

title: mom's summer pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the noodles, oranges, apple, celery and turkey.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice up the cucumbers.
Mix 2 gallons of water with 2 pounds of lime.
Add cucumbers and allow to soak or 24 hours.
Then, drain and rinse the cucumbers and place in ice water.
Allow to stand for 3 hours.
Make the syrup during this time by mixing all remaining ingredients well.
Drain pickles and pour syrup over top.
The next day, boil until the mixture is clear and place into canning jars.

title: apple hill cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sift together next 5 ingredients.
Add to apple mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake one hour in a preheated oven at 350°.
Sift a little powdered sugar over top in place of frosting.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix the next 4 ingredients and add to the first mixture; mix.
Do not beat!
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Stir cocoa and sugar together.
Melt butter and add other ingredients, one at a time.
Using mixer will give you a smooth consistency.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
except sausage and mix until like biscuits.
Separate
dough into 2 parts.
Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness.
Take
sausage
and
spread
over dough.
Roll into rolls
on waxed paper (like a jelly roll).
Chill.
Slice thinly. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Can be baked before and stored in tins.
Reheat in oven just before serving.

title: lemon pecan dainties
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg and lemon juice and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
Shape in 1 to 1 1/2-inch in diameter rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Chill.
May be left overnight in fridge.
Slice very thin; bake on greased cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: casey's apple pie
directions: Start heating oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch pie plate. Combine sugar, pie crust mix, cinnamon and nutmeg until crumbly. In pie plate, place applesauce; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Spread with crumbly mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until tender. Serve warm with cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make cornbread according to directions.
Let cool and crumble. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix with enough Miracle Whip or mayonnaise to be moist.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mama's canned green beans
directions: Wash, break and string the beans.
Blanch the beans.
Put beans into clean jars and fill to top with hot water along with salt.
Seal cans.

title: red potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes but do not peel.
Boil potatoes until fork-tender.
Drain.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Refrigerate until serving. Yields 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pineapple delight jello
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix pineapple and sugar in pan.
Bring to boil.
Add jello and stir.
Refrigerate until lightly jelled. Slowly add to softened cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pretty glass bowl and refrigerate.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Put eggs in double boiler.
Add vinegar and sugar, beating constantly until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool.
When cold, fold in whipped cream and fruit mixture. Leave in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Could add bananas, coconut and pecans too, if desired.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Mix mayo and sugar together.
Layer all other ingredients. Spread mayo mixture on top.
Garnish with a few of the leftover oranges.
Chill for about 30 minutes or serve immediately.

title: lemon chess pies
directions: Mix sugar, corn meal and flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: gold coast coffee
directions: In glass coffee maker, mix all ingredients except whipped cream.
Add spoon of whipped cream on top.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbled Ritz crackers on top.
Pour melted butter over mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain or chop ham in small pieces.
Cut bread and cheese into bite-size pieces.
Beat eggs a little.
Add all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle hash browns or corn flakes on top.
Let set 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Combine cake mix, egg whites, water and 2 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Beat for 2 minutes on high.
Reduce to low for 1 minute. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: baked mahimahi
directions: Lightly salt and pepper the fish.
Marinate in sherry for at least 1 hour.
Butter the pan.
Lay the fish down, then spread with mayonnaise, mixed with sliced onion.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well; add margarine and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Mix in vanilla and buttermilk alternately with sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites and pour into three 9-inch layer pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mix and forget beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and bake 3 to 4 hours at 350°.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: no cook mints
directions: Blend corn syrup, butter and extract with salt.
Add sugar and use hands to mix until smooth and well blended.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper to form a smooth paste.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add chicken and pour sauce over broccoli in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Put under broiler 2 to 3 minutes to brown.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brown veal in olive oil with 2 garlic cloves. Slice tomatoes in thick slices.
Add to veal, then add mushrooms.
Mix wine and cheese together.
Pour over meat and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine at room temperature.
Then mix with other ingredients.
Serve with fruit.

title: spiced pumpkin prune loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Beat in oil, sugar, pumpkin and prune juice.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices.
Add to pumpkin mix and stir until just blended.
Fold in prunes and nuts.
Evenly turn half batter into each of 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on rack 10 minutes. Turn out of pans and let cool.
Slice to serve. Makes 2 loaves.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer ingredients in dish.
Cook in covered dish in microwave until done.
Cooking time may range from 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix together and beat all ingredients at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Bake in long 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°.
Cool and ice.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Spray 10-inch quiche pan with butter flavored Pam.
Blend eggs, milk, melted margarine, flour, salt and pepper (can be done in a blender).
Add cheese, broccoli and mushrooms to mixture. Pour into quiche pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and slice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then dredge in flour.
Heat the bacon fat in a frying pan.
When the bacon fat is hot, add the tomatoes and brown on both sides.
As the tomato slices are done, remove to a serving platter.
Sprinkle with sugar and dot with butter.

title: syrian bread (round bun type)(talamee)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water.
Put flour, mahleb, sugar, salt, oil and melted butter in large mixing bowl.
Add dissolved yeast and warm water.
Mix well and knead, turning over until smooth, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cover with cloth and plastic and set in warm place for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours until dough doubles in size.
Cut into sections about the size of a grapefruit. Roll between cupped hands until smooth.
Cover and allow to rise about 30 minutes.
Flatten each ball to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cover with cloth and plastic and allow to rise for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Brush oil in baking pan and place dough on pan.
Bake until bottoms are light brown.
Place under broiler until top is lightly browned.
Yields 12 Talamee.

title: baked 4 bean casserole
directions: Mix beans with juices and all other ingredients in a baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
Great for a potluck.

title: chocolate mint wafer cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugars.
Blend in eggs.
Add water and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Leave in refrigerator 2 hours. Work dough around mint (flat, solid, chocolate mints) and place on greased cookie sheets.
Press pecan half on top if desired.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 350° oven.
Add rice and soup and cover. Bake for about an hour.

title: herbed tomato soup with pasta
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large Dutch oven.
Simmer over medium heat until potato is tender (15 minutes).
Add juice and pasta.
Simmer until pasta is tender.
Stir occasionally, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put in bowls and garnish with cheese and croutons.

title: zesty kabobs
directions: Marinate beef cubes in salad dressing for 4 to 8 hours. Remove and discard liquid.
Alternate vegetables and beef on skewers, leaving some space between each item.
Grill kabobs over hot coals until beef is desired doneness.

title: light-as-a-feather muffins
directions: Mix sugar and soft shortening thoroughly.
Blend in the egg. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in alternately with milk.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 23 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Place in 2-quart microwaveproof casserole; set aside.

title: vegetable dip #1
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve as a dip for fresh raw vegetables.
Yields 2 cups.

title: barbecue shrimp new orleans style
directions: Cook's Note: You can buy large, frozen tiger shrimp that have been deveined but are still in the shell. If you use these, thaw them according to the package directions. If using fresh shrimp, you can ask the person at the fish counter to devein them for you in the shell. You can also do this yourself: Using kitchen shears, cut the shell along the vein and pull the vein out with your fingers. Or, you can just skip the deveining process. The vein won't hurt you.

title: stroganoff superb
directions: Brown steak in oleo in large skillet.
Add onion, mushrooms and seasonings.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add cream cheese and milk.
Stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted. Serve over noodles.

title: *cornish hens
directions: Marinate raisins in sherry for 15 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add celery, onion and parsley and cook until tender. Add rice, orange juice, salt and marinated raisins; toss lightly. Sprinkle hens inside and out with salt and pepper as desired.
Rub with melted butter.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: glazed baked ham
directions: *Have butcher cut shank end off for split pea soup or whatever.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Mix by hand until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for
to 16 minutes (don't overbake), still bubbly. Meanwhile, melt 1 cup
chocolate chips or caramel chips and 2/3 cup peanut butter. Put on top of dough while still hot.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Use a big skillet, saute yellow onions in bacon drippings, cooking until limp but not brown. Add all other ingredients, except cabbage and cheese. Simmer about 25 minutes or until tomatoes are well cooked. Remove outer layers of cabbage, cut into serving size wedges, removing core. Boil 10 minutes in salted water. Drain and remove cloves and bay leaf from sauce. Put cabbage in a serving dish and pour sauce over the top with grated cheese. Bake at 400 degrees until cheese is melted. Serve steaming hot and pass the tabasco sauce.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Roll out dough on cutting board and cut with cookie cutters or knife. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown the roast in oil on all sides. Mix together mushroom soup and onion mix with water. Put your roast in a roasting pan and pour soup mixture over the meat; add celery and bell pepper on top and bake at 250 degrees for 3 hours. Add potatoes and carrots and bake 1 more hour or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Thaw strawberries partially and add strawberries, bananas, pineapple, blueberries and lemon juice to Jell-O.
Place 1/2 of mixture in bottom of large casserole. Congeal quickly in freezer about 30 minutes.
Spread the cup of sour cream over congealed mixture.
Add remaining gelatin and chill until firm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Use for braising or basting. Especially good on country style pork ribs.

title: aunt edie vandale's raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in 1 3/4 cups water for 5 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Moisten with remaining 1/2 cup water.
Add to raisins and stir until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon and butter.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch shell. Top with crust. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, jello, milk, oil and eggs; mix well.
Add strawberries, coconut and pecans; beat well.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: pumpkin nut roll
directions: Beat the eggs on high speed with an electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Gradually add the sugar.

Blend in the pumpkin and lemon juice. Stir together, then blend in the flour, cinnamon, baking powder, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Spread batter in a greased and floured jelly roll pan. Sprinkle with the nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn out onto a towel that has been covered with powdered sugar. Roll and cool.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth (I usually let set to rise until double and then.)
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Punch down. Turn out on lightly floured board.
Shape into rolls.
Bake in moderate oven, 350° to 375°, about 15 to 20 minutes.
(I usually punch down twice and let rise before shaping into rolls.)

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream the butter and sugar adding milk in small amounts.
Add salt and vanilla. Roll drained cherries in creamed mixture.
Take small ball and roll around cherries. Chill.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over heat and dip in chocolate mixture with toothpick.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Pour batter into prepared pans and bake for 55 minutes or until done.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs; mix dry ingredients and add to eggs. Add corn, cheese and pimiento. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 300° until set, about 45 to 50 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: czechoslovakian pastry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until combined.
In medium bowl mix salt with 3 1/2 c.
flour. Gradually add to butter mixture to form thick batter.
Spread 3/4 of the batter evenly over surface of an 11x17-inch jellyroll pan or cookie sheet with a rim.
Spread jam in even layer on top. Sprinkle nuts evenly over all.
Blend 1/4 c. flour with rest of dough.
Crumble on top.
Bake 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Cool completely and cut into bars.
Makes about 4 dozen bars.

title: golden butter frosting
directions: In a bowl combine butter and egg yolk.
Beat well.
Slowly blend in confectioners sugar.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Yields 3/4 to 1 cup.

title: redskin potatoes
directions: Wash and boil the potatoes until tender; quarter them.
Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Place the quartered potatoes in the pan.
Melt the cheese in the microwave; add the bacon bits, mayo and green onions.
Mix well.
Spoon over the top of the potatoes. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Brush with vegetable oil. Chop stems to make 1 cup.
In medium skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add mushroom stems and onions.
Saute 5 minutes until soft.
Place in mixing bowl with crabmeat, sour cream, egg, 1 cup bread crumbs, dill, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Spoon into mushroom caps.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add remaining bread crumbs. Sprinkle over each mushroom.
Bake in preheated oven until hot (350°).
Makes 18 stuffed mushrooms.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: I can remember only 3 real bad wind storms when I was growing up.
Two were tornados and one was a rolling wall of clouds that came straight from the west.

title: katy's cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Alternate adding flour and buttermilk, starting and ending with flour and beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Add boiling water and beat well.
Bake in largest size stem pan (one made all together is best) which has been greased and floured.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until golden brown.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla and almond flavoring. Add 1 cup of flour to 1/3 cup milk at a time, mixing well in between.
In the last 1/2 cup flour that is left add the baking powder and salt.
Add this last and blend well.
Flour tube pan and pour mixture into floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check, it may need 10 more minutes.

title: fruit jam cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except preserves in a mixing bowl. Beat with electric mixer on low until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups of mixture.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: custard pie(easy)
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in milk over low heat (just until dissolved).
Beat eggs and add to milk mixture with vanilla and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 15 minutes.

title: no-cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with foil. Chop peanuts.
Melt chocolate in a double boiler and pour into a bowl.
Melt peanut butter chips in a double boiler.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat melted peanut butter chips into cream cheese.
Press half the fudge into bottom of pan.
Spread melted chocolate over fudge in pan.
Freeze 5 minutes to set chocolate quickly.
Press remaining fudge over chocolate.
When set, cut into squares.
Calories per serving: 81.
Fat 2 grams.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Turn off heat. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover for 5 minutes.
Serve with corn chips or corn bread.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook on stove oleo, milk, sugar and cocoa.
Bring to a boil stirring continually for 10 to 15 minutes.
Take off heat and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon on wax paper.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: quick quiche
directions: Mix cheese and chilies; place on bottom of baking dish.
Pour Bisquick mixture (Bisquick, milk and eggs) over this.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Add those about an hour before serving.
Serves 8.

title: dessert
directions: Drain juice off canned fruit and mix all ingredients together. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: party slush drink
directions: Boil the Jell-O, water and sugar until dissolved. Add Cold Duck, pineapple juice, lemon juice and extract to this mixture. Mix all ingredients well.
Freeze mixture for 24 hours.
Remove from freezer the afternoon of your event.
Serve mixture as it reaches the slush stage. Re-freeze what you do not drink.

title: batter for deep frying
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until they are well blended. Dip vegetables, chicken or fish in batter before you deep fry them.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Flatten shrimp slightly; place into bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients except salt.
Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours, stirring shrimp once or twice.
Add salt to shrimp mixture; toss. Place shrimp on broiler pan.
Place marinade in small saucepan; heat to boiling.
Simmer 2 minutes or until hot.
Broil shrimp 3 inches from heat source 2 minutes; turn and cook 1 minute or just until cooked through.
Place on platter; pour hot marinade on top. Makes 4 servings.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut unpared potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place overlapping slices in buttered "oven-to-table" 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix butter and oil. Brush slices with mixture. Sprinkle with garlic, salt and thyme.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown at edges.
Mix once during baking time. Serves 4.

title: baked onions
directions: Cut end off onion and peel skin.
Slice onion 9/10 of the way through from top to bottom 4 to 6 times.
Put a slice of butter in each slit.
Sprinkle with Lemon-pepper after placing on a peice of foil approximately 12 x 12-inch square.
Pull edges of foil up slightly.
Pour approximately 1-2 Tbsp.
Worchestershire sauce into onion.
Fold foil and tightly cover onion.
Bake at 350° for 1-1 1/2 hours depending on the size of the onion.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Melt margarine; mix with flour.
Spread in pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water in a small bowl; let stand 2 minutes.
Place flour and salt in a food processor fitted with a steel blade.
Pulse twice to combine.
Add yeast mixture and combine with on-off turns until just moistened.
With machine running, pour oil through feed tube and process just until dough begins to leave sides of work bowl and form a ball.
Knead approximately 1 minute until smooth and elastic.
Form into a ball and place in oiled bowl, turning to oil top.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size (15 to 20 minutes).
Shape into pizza crust and proceed with your own topping recipe.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
One 12-inch pizza crust.

title: barb's zucchini bread
directions: *I use them sometimes, but not too much.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in bottom of pan.
Add batter and peaches.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pan stuffing
directions: Saute in 1 pound butter or margarine until celery and onions are transparent.

Add to 4 cups of chicken broth; stir until mixed. Then gradually add to bread cubes, tossing as you add the mixture. Season with poultry, chicken meat seasoning, add a little pepper. Place in roaster with cover or cover with foil.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 20 minutes to keep the stuffing from drying out around the edges.
A smaller amount will take less time to bake, but will still need to be stirred.

title: hillary's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda in large bowl.
Set aside.
With an electric mixer, beat together shortening, sugars and vanilla in large bowl until creamy.
Add eggs, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and rolled oats.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop batter by well-rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool cookies on sheets on wire rack for 2 minutes, then put cookies directly on rack to finish cooling.

title: chicken breast salad
directions: Salt chicken on both sides and brown in hot oil, about 5 minutes on each side.
Simmer in covered skillet until tender.
Do not overcook.
Cut in strips.
Prepare your favorite garden salad as desired.
Serve chicken over salad with dressing of your choice.
Serves 4.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, garlic, and onion together.
Stir in corn and let stand in refrigerator overnight, if possible.
Stir in Fritos right before serving.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: In large bowl, mix together all ingredients except sour cream. Pour 1/2 mixture into dish and refrigerate 1 hour.
Leave other half out.
When just about firm, spread on sour cream.
Place other half of mixture on top and refrigerate until serving.

title: almond balls
directions: Grind almonds that have been toasted at 200° (about 10 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients, mixing to a stiff paste. Form into 1/2-inch diameter balls.
Put on cookie sheet on foil or in cookie tin.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat dry jello and pineapple until jello is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese; fold well.
Chill until firm.

title: one-step creamed potatoes
directions: Parsley may be added if desired.

title: dipped chocolate drops candy
directions: Combine nuts, butter and coconut; mix well.
Add Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Sift in sugar.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate.
In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Stick toothpicks into balls and dip in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Store in airtight container.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Combine and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: heath bar coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugars and margarine until mixture is crumbly. Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Add remaining ingredients to dry mixture and beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry mixture, chopped candy and nuts over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until top springs back when touched.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and milk.
Pour into pie crust.
Slice bananas and place on top.
Drain pineapple and place on bananas. Cover pineapple with whipped topping and garnish with optional cherries and nuts.

title: apple crumble dessert
directions: Place apple slices in a 10-ounce glass custard dish.
Mix in flour, brown sugar and water.
Crumble cookie into 1/2-inch pieces onto apple slices.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until apple is tender.
Serve warm or cold, plain or with ice cream.
Makes about 1 serving with 225 calories.

title: yellow bean soup
directions: Combine first five ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.
Add kielbasa and cook 30 more minutes.
Mix flour with a little water to make a thick paste.
Add to sour cream and then mix into soup. Let come to a boil.
Leftovers freeze well.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Add baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, until mix is solid.
This means the mix will make a solid cookie ball.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add rice, prepared broccoli, soup and cheese.
Bake until light brown and bubbly in a 350° oven (approximately 25 to 30 minutes).

title: cookies (no-bake)
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk to boil.
Cook one minute.
Add rest of ingredients to hot mixture.
Stir vigorously until stiff.
Drop on wax paper.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Spread pineapple in bottom of 9x13 casserole dish.
Combine sugar, juice, and flour in small saucepan.
Bring to boil and stir 5 minutes.
Pour over pineapple.
Top with cheese.
Melt butter and mix with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over pineapple.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 25 minutes.

title: bacon quiche(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Bake pie shells at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
In large bowl, combine eggs, sour cream, Worcestershire and salt.
Blend well. Stir in cheese, bacon and onions.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Let boil 10 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add chocolate chips and Hershey bar. Stir until all is melted.
Fold in marshmallow cream and pecans. Pour into a 12 x 14-inch pan.
Let cool and cut into squares. Makes 5 pounds.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each. Add sour cream.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Fold into batter. Add flavorings.

title: fudge
directions: Combine milk, margarine and sugar in large saucepan and boil for 9 minutes.
Stir often to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Stir slowly until chips and Creme are dissolved.
Add nuts and stir at slow speed until nuts are covered.
Pour into buttered pan(s) and cool.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, dry gelatin and pineapple together.
Fold in oranges and whipped topping.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch dish.
Set in refrigerator for a while before serving.

title: ginger lime punch
directions: Mix together all but ginger ale and let stand for 2 hours. Add ginger ale before serving.
Makes 20 cups punch.

title: butter pecan fudge
directions: In large saucepan, bring oleo, half and half, granulated sugar, brown sugar and salt to boil over medium heat, stirring frequently. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in pecans and vanilla. Add powdered sugar and stir until smooth and well blended. Spread into 8 x 8 dish sprayed with Pam. Cool and cut into squares. Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Crush bananas with silver fork. Add eggs (beaten lightly), sugar, flour (sifted with salt and soda) and nut meats. Bake 1 hour in moderately slow oven (325°). Makes 1 loaf, 5 x 9-inches.

title: foiled cheese potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes, cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices of potatoes on a 20-inch length of aluminum foil.
Dash liberally with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese, cover with onions, then dot with butter.
Wrap and seal tightly.
Roast on grill or bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until tender.

title: the best pound cake
directions: Mix well together 3 sticks butter, sugar and cream cheese. Add one egg at a time, then mix flour, salt and flavors.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: puppy chow
directions: Combine the butter, peanut butter and chocolate morsels in a large microwaveproof bowl.
Heat on High for 1 minute.
Stir. Heat on High one additional minute.
Pour the cereal into another large bowl.
Pour the chocolate mixture over the cereal.
Stir to coat cereal with chocolate mixture.

title: tacos
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, drain and add all ingredients except beans and shells.
Stir well.
Mash beans or put them in blender and puree.
Add beans to meat sauce and simmer approximately 1 hour.
Put meat sauce in heated taco shells and top with your favorites.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add 2 cups hot water to Jell-O.
Let set until slightly thickened.
Stir in cranberry sauce and let set a while.
Fold in sour cream and nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: clove cake
directions: Stir; spread on cake and broil.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until done, stirring to crumble.
Drain well on paper towel.
Set aside.
Combine sausage and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a well greased 9x13 pan or baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake next morning at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes; saute with butter and onion.
Blend in flour; cook and stir milk in slowly.
Add salt.
Cook sauce until smooth. Put potatoes and sauce in greased casserole in alternate layers. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Cover first half hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel,
cook
and
mash	potatoes until creamy.	Stir in butter, sugar
and eggs, one at a time.
Add nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, reduce
to
325° and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer, or until a
knife
inserted	in the middle comes out clean.	This makes 3 (8 1/2 to 9-inch) pies.

title: southern living's caramel corn
directions: Coat 2 large baking pans with vegetable cooking oil spray.
In these pans, combine popcorn and pecans.

title: mom's ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water. Add ginger ale and chill until slightly thickened. Add peaches, celery and nuts and chill until firm.

title: hamburg noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with some onion.
Cook noodles.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole (beef and noodles).
Pour over tomato sauce. Cover with American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Combine butter, Parmesan cheese, egg, salt, pepper, garlic salt and oregano with cooked noodles.
Layer in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread cottage cheese over top of noodles. Brown meat and drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce, oregano and garlic salt.
Spread over the top of cottage cheese.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Then take out of oven and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake for an additional 10 minutes.

title: coca-cola roast
directions: Combine salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Rub over surface of roast.
Brown roast on all sides in oil.
Drain off drippings. Combine all other ingredients and pour over roast.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours or until tender.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg.
Combine flour, salt and soda and add to mixture.
Add buttermilk, rhubarb and nuts.

title: sweet chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over very low heat. Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, butter and vanilla; blend until butter is melted with the chocolate.
Stir in nuts.
Spread mixture into a lightly greased 8-inch pan immediately.
Cool at room temperature; cut into even squares.

title: toll house famous fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square baking pan with foil. Combine sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt in medium, heavy-duty saucepan. Bring to a full rolling boil over medium heat. Boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla. Stir until marshmallows are melted. Pour into prepared dish and refrigerate for 2 hours, until firm. Lift from pan and remove foil. Cut into pieces. Makes approximately 48 pieces.

title: thanksgiving cranberry jello salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water until they pop open.
Add Jell-O and sugar.
Mix until Jell-O dissolves.
Set until cool.
Add pineapple, celery, grapes and nuts.
Set.

title: smothered fried chicken
directions: Combine flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in buttermilk. Then dredge in flour mixture.
Brown chicken on both sides in hot oil over high heat.
Cover and reduce heat to low and cook 45 minutes or until done.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chocolate cream crunch
directions: Make crust by combining flour, pecans and margarine.
Mix well and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely. Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy. Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Blend well and spread on cool crust.
Chill.
Combine chocolate pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill. Repeat with vanilla pudding.
Chill.
Frost with remainder of whipped topping. Chill. Serve.

title: fried yellow squash
directions: Drop by tablespoon in hot fat and fry.

title: baked pleated potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and pat dry.
Cut each potato crosswise into 1/4-inch slices, cutting to but not through bottom of potato. Place on a baking sheet.
Combine oleo and remaining ingredients; brush over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done. Yield:
6 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Dissolve the baking soda in the applesauce and set aside. Cream together, until fluffy, the sugar, shortening and eggs. Combine all dry ingredients; add to the shortening mixture, alternating with the applesauce mixture.
Mix well.
Mix in vanilla.
Stir in the raisins.
Bake at 350° for one hour in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: carol's chicken salad
directions: Combine all and sprinkle almonds on top.

title: bean salad
directions: Do not drain beans.
Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add beans. Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Drain well before serving.

title: beef and noodle soup
directions: Put beef in hot water.
Add 2 tablespoons salt.
Let cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add water when needed.
Add the tomato puree, celery and onion.
When meat is done, add pepper and noodles. Cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions and slice about 3/8-inch thick; separate into rings.
Pour buttermilk into a shallow pan.
Add onion rings and allow to soak 30 minutes.
Combine egg, salt, baking powder, water, flour, 1 tablespoon salad oil, lemon juice and cayenne pepper; stir until smooth.
In a deep container, heat salad oil to 375°.
Remove onion rings from buttermilk and dip into batter; fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Spoon into a small oven-proof dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 2 cups.

title: crusty irish soda muffins
directions: Dry half a pound of good brown sugar, pound it, mix it with two pounds of flour and sift it.
Add 2 spoonfuls of yeast and as much new milk as will make it like bread.
When well risen, knead in half a pound of butter, make it in cakes the size of half a dollar and fry them to a light brown in hot oil.

title: baked rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the ingredients in a covered casserole.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes or longer for large quantities.
My favorite way to cook rice!

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in 1 1/2-quart microwave container. Cook on High for 20 to 22 minutes, stirring twice during cooking. While this is cooking, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Gradually pour hot mixture over egg whites in large bowl of mixer, beating on high.
Beat until mixture becomes thick and loses its gloss, about 12 minutes.
Add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen pieces.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix nuts, flour, oleo and vanilla well and pat into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven and cool.
Mix
cream cheese and cranberry sauce with mixer until well blended.
Add 3/4 of the Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts; mix well.
Pour into the cool nut crust.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top or around edges; sprinkle with nuts for garnish.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine shortening and sugar. Add egg, slightly beaten, in thirds to mixture. Blend in molasses. Add dry ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Dip top in sugar.
Place 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 7 or 8 minutes or until firm or lightly browned.

title: tuna divan
directions: Use a buttered 7 x 11-inch casserole.
Place drained, cooked broccoli stalks in casserole.
In a separate bowl, mix drained tuna, about 1 tablespoon lemon juice and the soup.
Spoon mixture over the broccoli.
Top with crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop fruits.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add lemonade and stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in Cool Whip and fold in fruit.
Pour into oiled individual molds or a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
You may also use a flat Pyrex dish.
Freeze until firm.

title: spicy microwave grilled chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasoning mix until well blended. Arrange chicken in 13 x 9-inch microsafe dish.
Brush with salad dressing mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Vent.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes, turning dish after 8 minutes.
Place chicken on grill over medium-hot coals.
Grill, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes on each side or until tender and brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: perfect fudge
directions: Cook stirring constantly over medium heat to a boil.
When boiling, stir 5 minutes.
Take off heat.
Stir in chocolate bits until completely melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: baking powder dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients together well until dough is quite thick.
Let stand for 15 minutes on floured board, then drop dough into boiling water.
Cover and boil for 20 minutes. Do not uncover or mix dumplings while cooking.
After 20 minutes, take out with a large slotted spoon and put on clean towel to dry out.
These dumplings are very light and tasty.

title: crackling bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar together and mix with cornmeal and bran.
Beat egg well; add milk and combine with dry ingredients, stirring only until flour disappears.
Add shortening and cracklings.
Bake in greased pan in moderate oven (400°) for about 40 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.
This is an old, old recipe.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream Blue cheese, Old English cheese and cream cheese together.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Roll into ball; roll in mixture of onion soup and nuts.
Can be divided into 2 or 3 smaller balls. Each will serve 30 to 40 people.

title: thanksgiving turkey
directions: This is for any size turkey so long as you have a roaster large enough to hold it with the lid tightly fitting; no foil cover please.
It will work with a gas or electric stove if your oven registers the correct temperature.

title: mama's famous pumpkin pies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Place pie shells into oven for 3 minutes.
Take out mix one at a time egg, pumpkin, spice, milk, sugar and flour (mix sugar and flour together before adding).
Mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, melted butter and 4 tablespoons sugar well.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes exactly.
Cool well.

title: donald's favorite blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and salt for 4 minutes.
Add baking powder and eggs.
Mix.
Add flour, milk and vanilla and mix again.
Add blueberries and walnuts.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In layers, place the ingredients in the pan in the following order: pineapple, cherry pie filling, dry cake mix and nuts.
Top with margarine slices and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: paydays
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil and remove from heat. Then add peanut butter, stir until creamy, Spanish peanuts, then add rice chex cereal.
Spread on sprayed cookie sheet, let cool slightly and cut into squares

title: ice cream with fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer. Pour into freezer container. Add 2 cups sweetened crushed peaches and 1 bottle Orange Crush. Stir well and freeze. Yield: 1/2 gallon plus 2 cups.

title: ahi pasta
directions: Heat oil in a large heavy skillet over medium/low heat.
Add onions and cook until translucent, stirring occasionally (about 5 minutes).
Add ahi, tomatoes, olives, basil and garlic; cook until ahi is opaque, stirring often, about 9 minutes.
Meanwhile cook linguine in a large pot of boiling water.
Drain well and put on warmed serving platter.
Spoon ahi mixture over pasta.
Garnish with capers and parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: ruby's chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken in small pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Saute onion in butter and put on chicken.
Prepare Stove Top dressing as directed and put over chicken.
Add soups and mix. Add broth.
Save a little dressing mix to sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese bean salad(no fat)
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar is clarified.
Drain all veggies; mix together and pour vinegar/sugar mixture over all. Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least for 6 hours.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish or pan, about 9-inch square. Add peaches and syrup.
Mix flour, sugar and milk with mixer in separate bowl.
Pour over peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Place a spoonful of mixture in each lasagna noodle, roll and place in baking dish.
Cover with cheese sauce and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until done.

title: corn fritters
directions: Cook corn in salted water; drain off liquid.
Reserve 1 cup liquid.
Add butter in saucepan; add flour and cook.
Stir rapidly until smooth and rolls away from sides of pan.
Remove from heat. Add eggs, 1 at a time, and really stir.
Add corn.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot oil; cook until golden brown and puffy. Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Boil and debone chicken.
Mix all ingredients and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in a thin pan (pizza pan size).
Top with other ingredients, starting with lettuce, tomatoes and
top with cheese.
Scoop up with nachos.

title: grandpa's barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil.

title: beef goulash with gherkins(warms the house and the body)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat lard in 5-quart flameproof casserole until a light haze forms, then add onions.
Cook over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Off the heat, stir in the paprika, coating onions well.
Add the beef and pour the wine and beef stock over it.
Stir in salt and a few grindings of pepper.
Bring to a boil; cover tightly and bake in middle of oven for 1 hour. Remove casserole from oven and with a spoon, skim off about 2 tablespoons of the surface fat.
Combine this with the
2 tablespoons of flour; stir the mixture into the casserole.
Return casserole to oven and cook 30 to 40 minutes longer, or until beef shows no resistance when pierced with the tip of a small sharp knife.
Skim surface fat from the casserole; add the gherkins and heat for 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Taste for seasoning.
Serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch greased pan (dish).

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Fill a large dish half full of shredded lettuce.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Add layer of frozen cooked peas which have been chilled.
Cover completely with 1 pint Miracle Whip. Add 8 ounces shredded cheese and 1/2 pound cooked and crumbled bacon.
Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: ginger-upper(only 93 calories per serving.)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add lemon juice and ginger ale.
Chill until very thick. Add pears. Spoon into molds. Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Makes 3 cups or 6 servings.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Cream together butter with shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each egg is added.
Sift flour in baking powder and salt.
Add this alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Bake in a large tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Will freeze well.

title: cheesy chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix together cooked noodles, sour cream and cream cheese.
Mix soups, tomatoes and chicken.
Alternate layers of noodle mixture, soup/chicken mixture and cheese.
End with cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Stew and debone chicken.
Reserve broth.
Place deboned chicken in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix broth and soup together. Pour over chicken.
Season to taste.
Add drained vegetables.

title: portuguese soup
directions: In a large pot, fry bacon until fat is rendered.
Add onion, celery, carrot, garlic and potato; saute all until bacon is crisp and vegetables are golden.
Add sausage, tomatoes, tomato sauce, kidney beans, broth, peppercorns, bay leaf and cinnamon.
Cook until cabbage is done.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: barbecued mullet
directions: Have backbone and head removed from a large fresh mullet, leaving scales on the fish. Open fish and salt well; place scale side on hot charcoal fire. Baste open sides of fish every few minutes with sauce.

title: cheryl's chocolate date nut cake
directions: Cook dates in water and 1 teaspoon soda; cool and set aside. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and 3/4 teaspoon soda together.
Alternate flour and date mixture until well mixed.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in batter; put topping on batter.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line pan with Reynold's Wrap and 1/2 cup of water and butter.
Let melt and mix together.

title: merry cherry bars(christmas cookies)
directions: Beat together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in egg and almond extract.
Combine flour and salt and mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup candied cherries.
Spread dough into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cherries and M&M's; press in lightly.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Cool thoroughly.
Combine powdered sugar and water.
Mix until smooth.
Drizzle over top. Cut into bars.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Prepare 6 servings of grits according to instructions on package.
Stir in chunks of cheese and butter until melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in 1/4 pint whipping cream or enough to make it soupy.
Pour in casserole dish and top with crushed Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chunky chippers(adam's favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Sift first three ingredients on waxed paper or in small bowl.
Cream next 7 ingredients.
Add flour mix and chocolate chips.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs
and beat.
Add flour, soda, milk, vanilla and mashed bananas; beat.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350°.

title: sooner buttermilk pie
directions: In a bowl mix together the buttermilk, flour and melted butter.
Blend until flour is mixed in.
Add the sugar and the eggs while beating the mixture.
Add lemon extract and continue to mix.
Heat oven to 425° and prepare the crust.
Place the filling mixture in the crust and sprinkle the cinnamon on top.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce the oven heat to 350° and bake for 25 additional minutes.
Make sure filling is set.
Let cool and serve warm or chilled.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Cook noodles according to directions. In large skillet, brown beef and onion over medium heat, then drain. Add spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and Italian seasoning. Drain noodles. In a 5-quart crock-pot, spread a third of the meat sauce. Cover with a third of the noodles and pepperoni. Sprinkle with a third of the cheeses. Repeat layers twice. Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours or until heated through and cheese is melted. Yield 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add zucchini, then flour and cinnamon.
Stir in nuts or raisins.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour or until done at 350°.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.

title: bacon stuffed tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, reserving 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Crumble 5 slices of bacon and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in bacon drippings.
Wash and cut tops off tomatoes. Spoon out tomato pulp.
Cook over low the tomato pulp, onion and celery until tender.
Add bacon crumbs, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and peas reserving liquid in bowl. In skillet, melt butter. Put in enough flour to make a paste. Add juice from asparagus and peas to make gravy. In casserole dish, layer peas, asparagus, egg and cheese then pour gravy on. Crumble crackers over top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, then mix together ketchup, chilies and onion.
Spread over chicken. Sprinkle cheeses over top.
Bake additional 10 to 15 minutes to melt cheese.

title: brandi's brownies
directions: In small bowl, beat together at medium speed the eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla for about 1 minute until light.
Add melted butter.
Continue beating until thoroughly blended.
Mix flour and cocoa together and add to creamed mixture.
Spread evenly in greased 8-inch square dish.
Microwave at High (10) for 6 to 7 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes.
When done, top looks dry and will spring back when lightly touched.
Cool and cut. Makes about 20 brownies.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Add water to egg yolks.
Beat 5 minutes.
Add sugar.
Beat 5 minutes.
Add flour. Beat 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and salt.
Fold in egg whites.
Place in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut squash lengthwise.
Scoop out center and dice.
Set shells aside.
In 12 inch skillet cook meat, onion and diced zucchini until meat is browned and vegetables are tender, adding oil if necessary.
Stir in oregano, pepper and half of tomato sauce, half of cheese, 3/4 tsp. of salt.
Remove from heat.

title: chocolate-butterscotch treats
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Add nuts and noodles; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: pecan or cashew brittle
directions: In 2-quart glass measure, microwave on High the syrup and salt 2 to 3 minutes to boiling. Cook 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts, margarine, vanilla and cinnamon. Cook 2 minutes.
Immediately stir in soda until light and foamy. Quickly pour onto greased cookie sheet or jelly roll pan. Spread, cool and break into pieces.

title: christmas coffee cake
directions: Butter an angel food cake pan.
Place frozen rolls in bottom of pan.
Mix together pudding (dry), sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Sprinkle on nuts.
