Pour melted butter over top. Cover (with dry dish towel) and let set on counter overnight. Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Put oleo in bowl and mix at medium speed.
Add sugar, salt and extract.
Add one egg at a time.
Sift in flour and beat 15 minutes after all ingredients are added.
Bake in an ungreased tube or loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake first 30 minutes at 300° and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken sausage gumbo
directions: Mix garlic powder, cayenne pepper, black pepper and salt with the flour.
Roll the chicken pieces in the flour mixture.
Brown in deep fat; drain.
Save the extra flour mixture.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Brown bacon, ground beef and chopped onions in a frying pan. Mix all together; bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: green chili soup
directions: Saute salt pork slowly.
Add onion, pork and garlic until cooked.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours.

title: cheddar squash cloverleaf rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve sugar in water.
Sprinkle the yeast over the water and stir gently.
Let stand until light and foamy.
Stir in milk, 3 tablespoons butter, salt, squash and cheese.
Add enough flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface; knead until dough is no longer sticky (about 5 minutes).
Form into a ball and place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about
1 hour.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook zucchini in chicken broth until tender (10 to 12 minutes). In blender combine hot zucchini, broth and jalapeno cheese and blend until smooth.
According to your taste, either the mild or hot Mexican Velveeta cheese may be used.
This soup is equally good served hot or cold.
Makes 4 to 5 cups of soup.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and mash with electric mixer.
Beat in creams. Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into greased round dish. Sprinkle with butter and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Blend flour, shortening and sugar together.
Dissolve yeast in water; mix with hands.
Roll into balls (three).
Put each ball in muffin tin to form a cloverleaf.
Makes 12 rolls.
Let rise 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: potato and cheese
directions: Mix
potatoes,	sour cream, soups, cheese, salt, pepper and onion
together.
Put
in
pan.
Sprinkle
with Parmesan. Saute corn flakes in 1/2 stick margarine and put on top.	Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
While heating, mix cornstarch with small amount of water.
Add egg yolks to cornstarch and mix well.
Pour into hot milk and stir while cooking on low to medium heat.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or whipped cream.

title: chicken caruso
directions: Coat chicken in flour.
Heat oil in skillet.
Brown chicken on one side; turn and start to brown other side.
After turning, add all remaining ingredients in order listed.
Simmer on stove top until sauce is slightly thickened and cheese has melted.

title: hanky panky hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cook all meat.
Add seasoning; drain well.
Add cheese.
Melt. Spread on bread.
Broil until toasted brown, bubbly hot.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of crumb mixture in 9-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb.
Combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until clear and pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: NOTE:
No directions were given - just a list of ingredients.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in top container of double boiler. Add water and vinegar gradually. Add eggs and cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat. Add butter and cool thoroughly. Blend in salad dressing and mustard. Store in refrigerator. Keeps for weeks. Makes 1 quart.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Peel onions.
With a tablespoon, scoop out the center of each onion.
Place 1 bouillon cube in center.
Add 2 tablespoons of cheese and place 1 ice cube on top.
Take square of heavy-duty foil and bring up around onion, twisting at top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes, or until tender (pierce with fork to test).

title: connie locke's cheese ball
directions: Mix together all the ingredients, except for Parmesan cheese or nuts.
Once mixed together, form a log or a ball and then roll in Parmesan cheese or nuts.

title: red pepper broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets.
Combine dressing and all ingredients in plastic container.
Toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours, shaking occasionally to coat.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: rice, broccoli, cheese casserole
directions: Mix all in ovenproof dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Chop onions fine. Cook in butter or oleo until soft, but not brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Makes enough to stuff a 12 pound bird.

title: phil's beef stew
directions: Brown beef in oil; sprinkle with garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour off excess grease.
Add tomatoes and one cup of water; add additional Worcestershire sauce if desired. Let simmer for about 45 minutes.
Put in carrots and rutabaga and cook for 20 minutes and add onions.
About 10 minutes later, add potatoes.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Stir in mushroom soup and blend well.

title: hot cabbage salad
directions: Cook sliced cabbage and caraway seeds in saltwater about 20 minutes; drain well.

title: crab soup
directions: Simmer all except butter, Worcestershire sauce, flour and mustard for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Melt butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and add to soup.
Cook an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, egg, cheese, onion and mushroom soup.
Arrange cooked broccoli spears in Pammed oblong casserole dish.
Pour mixture over.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
(Does not double well.)

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add fruit juices, cook until smooth and pour in the well beaten egg.
May thin with a little cream; if needed.

title: easy corn bread dressing
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until tender.
Add to rest of ingredients and toss lightly until bread is thoroughly moistened. Put in 8-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix. Pour over oleo in an oblong dish.
Spread fluid over cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla extract until light and fluffy; add flour and nuts and blend well.
Chill the dough while you take the foil off the kisses.
Roll the dough around the kisses.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 12 to 14 minutes at 375° in center of the oven.
Remove to wire rack.
While warm sprinkle confectioners sugar over cookies.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together well and chill.

title: oatmeal raisin muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the oats and buttermilk.
Let the mixture stand for 1 hour.
Stir in the eggs, sugar and the butter. Sift the flour with the baking powder, salt and soda.
Add the flour mixture
to the egg mixture and stir the mixture until it is combined.
(The batter will be lumpy.)

Fold in the raisins. Spoon the batter into 12 well buttered and floured 1/3 cup muffin tins. Bake the muffins in a preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in the centers comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: ensalada enchilada
directions: Chop ingredients separately (not mushy).
Toss ingredients and season to taste.
Do not mix cheese in.
Roll chopped ingredients into a lettuce leaf.
Top with shredded cheese.
Serves 4.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: For success, do this first:
Have ingredients room temperature.
In hot weather, use buttermilk and eggs directly from refrigerator.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and dust with flour 3 round layer pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inch.

title: curry chilli
directions: In large saucepan, add meat and sauce over medium heat.
Add 2 cups Curry King.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans and cook for additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.
Serve with rice, Indian bread or pita bread or over hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: lime jello sherbet
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar.
Cool.
Add other ingredients.
Freeze.
Stir 3 to 4 times during freezing. When soft frozen, beat with rotary beater.
Return to refrigerator trays until ready to serve.

title: old english pies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Blend in all other ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites real stiff and fold in. Divide into 2 pie shells.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: my mother's date-nut bread #1
directions: Blend together dates, water, butter, salt, sugar and molasses. Add flour, soda, cream of tartar, egg and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes until straw inserted comes out clean.

title: easy as 1-2-3 microwave potatoes
directions: Quarter several Irish potatoes in a bowl.
Sprinkle with all of the seasoning and several pats of butter.
Cover with Saran Wrap; cook in the microwave on High for 8 or 10 minutes.
Take out; pour Ranch dressing over potatoes until they are well coated. Put back in microwave and finish cooking, probably 8 to 10 more minutes.
Super delicious!

title: double chocolate brownie bars
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, stir together sweetened condensed milk, chocolate pieces and salt and cook until smooth. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Put 2/3 of cookie dough over bottom of ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread chocolate mixture over dough.
Dot with remaining cookie dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces in a bowl. Break apart cauliflower into small pieces and mix with the lettuce and peas.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender and process until smooth.
Yields 1 1/4 cups, equivalent to 1 (14 ounce) can.
Store in refrigerator until needed.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening together very well.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add eggs.
Combine cake flour and baking powder and alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 315° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Layer dips in bottom of dish.
Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning together.
Layer over bean dip and guacamole. Layer remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve with chips.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Melt the first butter in a heavy 2-quart saucepan. Blend in the flour, salt and pepper, stirring until well mixed.
Remove from heat. Add chicken broth and milk.
In a separate pan, melt second butter and saute the chopped mushrooms.
Season with onion salt. Add to the milk mixture.
Simmer about 10 minutes on low heat until all flavors are blended. Stir constantly. Serve hot. Serves 6.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Into 1 cup boiling water, add shortening, sugar and salt.
When cool, add eggs and cold water and beat.
Add yeast and flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise until doubled in size and knead down.
Cut in rolls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into an 8-inch dish and add about 1/3 of the zucchini, onion, Mozzarella, Parmesan cheese, salt to taste and parsley.
Make layers in this manner until all ingredients are used.
Cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, until golden brown, approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients as for pie crust in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°; let cool.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream margarine, eggs
and sugar.
Stir in flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Roll into balls and roll in mixture of sugar and sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: sweet drop biscuit dough
directions: Blend or sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; cut in finely shortening and add egg and milk. Stir with a fork to make a drop batter. Use pastry as directed for Fresh Berry Cobbler, (Recipe in Dessert Section). Cobbler can be made with fresh strawberries, blueberries, raspberries. It can be used with canned fruit as well, (Cherries, pineapple chunks, peaches, blueberries, raspberries in 20 ounce cans of sweetened fruit are suggestions.)

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute the onion in the oleo or butter.
Add the remaining ingredients, except broccoli.
Heat until cheese has melted.
Add drained broccoli.
Freezes well.
Delicious.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Roll crackers fine using rolling pin.
Mix all ingredients well and put in greased pan.
Refrigerate.

title: eggnog quick bread
directions: To Make Bread:
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, eggnog, margarine, rum extract and vanilla.
Blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg to creamed mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Note: Mix by hand!

title: potato mushroom casserole
directions: Mix and stir first 5 ingredients.
Stir in milk and potatoes. Pour into a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish (covered).
Top with 1/4 cup grated cheese and bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, stock and butter.
Microwave on High 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Mix in cream and serve.

title: basic white bread
directions: Put water in large bowl, empty content of yeast package into it.
Add sugar and salt, stir well until yeast is completely dissolved.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring in with wooden spoon until smooth dough is made.
Melt butter, mix into dough. Add remaining flour.
Continue stirring or mixing until dough is thoroughly blended.
Turn dough out onto floured board and cover with inverted bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Knead about 3 minutes until dough is elastic and satiny.
Put into bowl and cover with a towel.
Place in warm spot.
Let rise 1 hour and 30 minutes to 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Pouch down firmly 2 or 3 times. Turn out onto floured board and knead 3 minutes.
Divide into 2 equal parts and shape into loaves.
Put each into well buttered pans.
Cover and allow to rise.
When loaves have doubled in bulk, bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Prepare brownie batter according to package directions, but do not bake.
Cut a circle of parchment paper to fit a 15 inch round baking stone.
Pour brownie batter onto parchment paper and spread evenly into a 14-inch circle.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until brownie is set.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely.

title: hush puppies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients; beat egg with half of water.
Stir into cornmeal mixture.
Stir in onion and just enough water to make a thick batter.
(Batter should drop, not pour from spoon.)
Heat oil to very hot.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls into the hot oil.
Cook uncovered about 3 minutes.

title: funny cakes
directions: Mix together the 4 ingredients.
Put on stove and boil until well mixed.
Let cool before pouring into pie shell.

title: crab cakes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil until barely soft; drain.
Set aside (mashed).
Saute celery and onion in butter until barely soft.
Add celery and onion to potatoes.
Add crab meat and seasoning (seasoning will vary according to taste).
Form into cakes and place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Place under broiler for 1 minute to brown before serving.

title: golden angel delight
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat apricots and blend into gelatin.
Add lemon juice, powdered sugar and salt.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Whip until frothy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Split angel food loaf into 2 or 3 layers.
Fill between layers and frost.
Chill several hours.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Microwave or bake chicken until mostly done.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with pizza sauce, then Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for an additional 20 minutes.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Combine warm water and yeast.
Cut shortening into flour and sugar.
Add milk.
Add the yeast water mixture.
Blend in eggs. Cover; place in refrigerator overnight.
Spread with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar mixture.
Roll lengthwise.
Slice and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: ice cream
directions: Cook all ingredients, except the fruit, over medium high heat, stirring constantly until mixture will coat a wooden spoon.
Fill canister to mark and cool.
When cooled, put canister in ice cream churn.
Add ice and rock salt; churn until churn is hard to turn or, if electric, when it slows down.
When mixture gets firm, add fruit. Drain some of the water out of the churn.
Put plastic over ice cream; pack ice over the canister.
Let set for several hours to "cure."

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Stir all ingredients in a bowl with fork until moistened, beat vigorously 1 minute.
Pour into pan and bake until pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sherbet.
Drop sherbet in large scoops into punch bowl.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Beat the egg white with salt until very stiff.
Gradually add brown sugar and vanilla while still beating.
Fold in chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a buttered and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Cookies should be a light brown.

title: strawberry 'n cream squares
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add berries, stirring occasionally until thawed.
Add pineapple and banana.
Pour half mixture in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: date squares
directions: Mix in bowl with fingers.
Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan. Use half of the mixture.
Pat in greased pan, then add Filling (recipe to follow).
Cover Filling with the rest of the crumb mixture, pressing down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice frittata
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook onions in butter until tender.
Beat eggs with milk and seasonings.
Stir in rice, chilies and tomato.
Pour in pan.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover.
Cook until top is almost set, 12 to 15 minutes. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: barbecued deer steaks
directions: Cover steaks with milk; let stand 30 minutes.
Remove from milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour; brown in butter. Place layer of steaks in casserole.
Add layer of onion and barbecue sauce.
Repeat layers until all steaks are used.
Pour wine over steaks.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: soft hermit cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and salt. Mix well. Mix baking soda and applesauce. Add to creamed mixture. Add in remaining ingredients. Mix well. Spread in greased 9x4x2 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 min. Keeps well. Makes 24.

title: biscotti chocolate chip(italian chocolate chip cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Line cookie sheets with paper bags or kitchen parchment.
Best to leave eggs out overnight and do early next morning.
Beat egg whites until they are stiff.
Gradually add sugar; reduce speed and beat half an hour.
Then mix in by hand the ground hazelnuts.
Heap by teaspoonful onto prepared cookie sheets. Place a whole hazelnut on the top of each cookie (press in a little).
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes.
Let set on trays for 2 hours in a warm area.
The cookie should not be sticky to the touch.
If they are, let set additional time before baking.
Makes approximately 80 to 100 cookies.

title: ham strata with broccoli
directions: Cut 12 doughnut shapes and holes from bread.
Fit remaining scraps of bread with a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange cheese, broccoli and ham in layers, topping with bread doughnuts and holes.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over all.
Cover, refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Blend jello, water and lemon juice.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: chocolate-oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil oleo, sugar, milk and cocoa evenly 1 1/2 minutes.
Time by the clock.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Drop on wax paper.

title: north dakota buns
directions: Soften
yeast
in
warm water.
Mix flour, salt, sugar, dry milk
and shortening like a pie crust until like cornmeal. Pour liquid
over
dry
mixture.
Stir
in 2 well beaten eggs. Let sit 10
minutes.
Knead
until elastic.
Let rise 1 hour. Punch down and let rise.
Make buns about the size of an egg. Let rise until light on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Buns freeze well.

title: microwave tuna casserole
directions: In a microwave-safe casserole, combine tuna fish, soup, peas and onion.
Mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 6 minutes. Stir after 3 minutes. Sprinkle potato chips on top before serving. Serves 4.

title: deluxe yellow cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease two 9-inch layer pans.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and cream thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Add alternately the flour in three portions.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Allow to cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: hazel's spiced percolator tea
directions: Put spices in basket.
Pour juices in bottom and perk.

title: piquant scallops
directions: Separate scallops and sprinkle with salt.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Arrange scallops in greased scallop shells or in a shallow greased baking dish.
Melt butter and add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour sauce over scallops.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble and drain; prepare 9-inch pie shell.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in shell.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 or 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 or 8 servings.

title: baby baked sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and core apples.
Slice apples and mix sweet potatoes and apples in baking dish.
Pour liquid over. Bake in microwave for 5 to 8 minutes, then mash with a fork.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter, mix sugars together, mix butter, eggs, milk and chopped nuts.
Then combine with sugars & raisins, etc.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and quick oats.
Stir together, then combine with liquid mixture.
Make sure all flour is mixed in.
Place round 2-inch balls on baking sheet approximately 2-inch apart.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375.
Preheat oven. 12 minutes is my time.
Remove and cool for 1 minute and remove from sheet to cooling rack.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Peel onions but do not cut off root end.
Cut a 1-inch slice from the top (leave root intact).
Place onions in a large pot of boiling water (salted) and simmer over medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes until just tender.
Drain onions and allow to cool.
When cool enough to handle scoop out onion leaving about 1/2 inch attached to the root.
Invert on paper towel and allow to drain. Chop the center meat of the onions.
In a bowl mix bread crumbs, cheese, nuts, egg, butter, parsley, basil, garlic salt, pepper and onions.
Stuff drained onion cups with mixture.
Arrange filled onions in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend soup with milk and whipping cream.
Pour around, not over, onions.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until tops are browned. Serves 6.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa until blended, then add milk and syrup. Place over heat and bring to a boil until a drop of this forms a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter; let set until cold.
Beat until candy is thick; add nuts, then pour into buttered pan and cut squares when firm

title: cherry squares
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Blend flour and margarine until it is like pie dough.
Add yeast mix, cooled milk and sugar.
Roll thin (1/2-inch) and put half of dough on cookie sheet with sides. Cover with fruit filling, then top with other half of dough.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned (about 30 minutes).
When cool, frost and cut into squares.
Other fruits may be used equally well.

title: chicken sicilian(degiovani restaurant)
directions: Flour chicken breasts lightly.
Put olive oil (about 2 tablespoons) in pan.
Add garlic and chicken; saute until brown. Add white wine, chicken broth, butter, olives, sun-dried tomatoes and roasted red pepper.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover; cook for about 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook until sauce is a little dry.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 2 people.

title: pecan caramels
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, 1 cup half and half, corn syrup and butter.

Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil (7 to 8 minutes). Add remaining 1 cup half and half; continue cooking, stirring often, until mixture reaches 245° (35 to 40 minutes).
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cover; refrigerate 1 to 1 1/2 hours to cool.
Cut into 64 pieces.
Drop 1/4 teaspoon melted chocolate on top of each caramel; press pecan half into chocolate.
Cover; store refrigerated.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine Ranch dressing mix with sour cream and salad dressing. Pour over chopped vegetables and chill overnight.
This will keep for several days.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (cottage cheese, can of fruit, Jell-O and Cool Whip).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add melted margarine; mix well. Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; mix well.
Pour into pie shell (deep dish) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test after 45 minutes by lightly touching about 2 inches from edge of crust.
If firm, it's done.
Makes 1 large or 2 small.

title: patchwork coleslaw
directions: Mix up desired quantities.

title: the best chicken
directions: Take the number of skinless, boneless chicken breasts that you need, usually one per person.
Lay the breasts in a baking pan. Sprinkle with dry Lipton onion soup mix, one package or more or less depending on the number of chicken pieces.
Blend one can of cream of chicken soup, a tablespoon or two of sour cream, if you have it (optional), and a half or full can of milk.
(Depends on how many pieces of chicken you are doing.
You will need to make enough sauce to cover all the pieces.
If you are doing a lot, maybe you'll need to use two cans of soup.)
Pour this over the chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° to 350° until the chicken in done.
If the sauce curdles, spoon off and put in blender and blend until smooth, then pour back over chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and celery, drain.
Add seasonings, corn, beans, olives, soup and cheese. Mix well.
Mix corn bread topping according to package directions.
Pour over casserole and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a large loaf pan and bake for about 1 hour at 325°.
This recipe is over 100 years old.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Stew chicken or use turkey.
Fill 2 cups with bite size pieces.
Mix in celery and almonds.
In another bowl, mix mayonnaise and soup.
Combine both mixtures.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Poke holes in bag of chips with fork to let air out.
Crush chips with hand before opening bag.
Put chips on top of mixture.
Bake approximately 40 minutes.
About 5 or 10 minutes before it's done, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil peppers 5 minutes. Brown ground beef. Add onion. Cook macaroni and rice. Let cool. Place peppers in casserole dish. Combine all ingredients. Place mixture in peppers. Pour tomato soup or tomato sauce over top. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together just before frying. Do not stir any more than absolutely necessary. Drop by tablespoonfuls into oil in electric frying pan or deep fryer heated to 400°. Cook about 4 minutes on each side until hush puppies are golden brown. Drain on paper towels and keep warm.

title: copper carrots
directions: Heat together for a few minutes and pour over cooked carrots, onion and pepper.
Cover good so steam can't get out as this cooks the onion and pepper.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground meat and spices with onion, bell pepper and celery.
Add tomatoes, 1/2 can water, and 1/2 can uncooked rice. Pour into greased casserole and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cover for first 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: You will need 1 deep oblong baking dish or pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix beef, tomato sauce, onion, bread, egg and seasoning.
Spread in a 10-inch heavy skillet.
Cover with 1/2 cup ketchup.
Bake 1 hour.

title: working girl stew
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add other ingredients; cook until done.

title: pickled jalapenos
directions: Wash jalapenos and pack tightly in clean jars.
Mix vinegar, water, olive oil, salt and mixed pickling spices.
Bring to a boil. Pour over jalapenos.
Seal.
Process in water bath for 10 minutes.
Remove from hot water.
Let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello popcorn
directions: Boil the sugar, syrup, jello and food coloring 1 minute.
Put 3 quarts popcorn in large bowl; do same with other 3 quarts popcorn.
Pour syrup mixture over corn.
Butter hands; make popcorn balls.
Use orange jello and coloring for Halloween, red or green jello and coloring for Christmas.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese and artichokes.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 325° to 350°, until bubbly and lightly browned.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Add sugar, salt and milk; stir constantly.
Cook a few minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Serve warm on ice cream or for a topping on other desserts.

title: mexican chicken bake
directions: Combine chicken, tomatoes, onions, chilies and cumin.
Mix well.
Blend sour cream, 3/4 cup Cheddar, Monterey Jack and egg. Spread half the corn chips in casserole.
Layer with half chicken mixture and half the sour cream mixture.
Repeat and top with remaining chips and 1/4 cup Cheddar.
Bake until done.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and half the flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening. Gradually beat in the rest of the flour until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth and place in refrigerator at least 4 hours or overnight.
Cut into 6 parts.
Roll each part out and cut into 8ths.

title: fusilli with sweet corn
directions: In a large pot, bring 5 quarts (5 l) salted water to a boil.

title: fried rice
directions: Combine onion and margarine in saucepan.
Place bouillon in hot water until dissolved.
Add rice and green onion to all ingredients and place in a casserole.
Cover and microwave at High 4 to 8 minutes.
Let stand, covered, until liquid is absorbed, 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir in eggs and soy sauce.
Microwave, uncovered, at High until eggs are set, 2 to 4 minutes, stirring several times.
Fluff with fork before serving.

title: santa fe chicken chowder
directions: Combine margarine and flour to make roux; set aside.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake brownies
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan with 1 roll of the sliced dough to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Beat cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla in mixer. Spread over crust.
Top with remaining roll of sliced dough.
Bake 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: homemade peanut butter
directions: Put the peanuts in a blender.
Add a little oil.
Blend together.
Add the rest of the oil.
Blend until smooth.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Heat milk and a pat of butter, add stuffing mix. Mix with hamburger, egg, salt, sugar, allspice, pepper, onion and celery. Roll into small balls and brown in butter.

title: curried chicken
directions: Saute onion and curry powder in margarine. Blend in next 4 ingredients.
Add broth and milk gradually.
Cook, stirring until thick.
Add bite size chicken pieces and lemon juice.
Heat through and serve over cooked rice.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until thick.
Add lemon juice, water and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Cool. Beat egg whites until stiff with sugar and continue beating until like Marshmallow Creme.
Fold half of meringue into lemon mixture. Pour into pie crust and spoon rest of meringue in ring around outside of pie crust.

title: pizza rice casserole
directions: Brown the beef and onion together, then add the spaghetti sauce.
Combine the cooked rice and cottage cheese.
Layer rice and meat mixtures in a casserole dish, making the top layer the sauce.
Top with the shredded cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Toast 1/3 cup chopped pecans in 1 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Set aside for topping.

title: rolls
directions: Crust:
Use 2 crust recipe.
Use a 9 x 11-inch baking dish. Roll 2/3 of dough to fit dish.
Leave extra crust to fold over top.
Roll out rest of crust for top crust.

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns for 30 minutes.
Mix ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: hershey peanut butter cups
directions: You will also need cupcake papers.
You may want to double this.

title: baked salmon in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil over medium heat until hot.
Add spinach, tomatoes, onion, and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until mixture is thick and onion is tender.
In medium skillet, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil until hot.
Add salmon; cook 1 to 2 minutes until lightly browned.
Place 1/4 of spinach mixture in center of each piece of foil; top with salmon steak.
Drizzle liquid from skillet over salmon.
Top each with lemon slice and parsley.
Fold edges of each foil square together.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and press together where perforated.
Bake as per directions on package.

title: stone (vegetable) soup
directions: Chop raw vegetables and put in large pot.
Add tomatoes, frozen vegetables and water as needed.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 3 hours.
Taste and add salt and pepper.
Taste again and adjust if needed.
Refrigerate overnight. Heat and enjoy.

title: quick and easy goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion until done.
Drain while cooking macaroni.
Drain and clean pan.
Combine macaroni, hamburger and onion mixture, tomato sauce and cheese sauce.
Stir thoroughly and simmer 5 minutes on low heat.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve cold.
Serves 50.

title: roasted red pepper sauce
directions: In a blender, combine red peppers, olive oil, lemon juice, vinegar, water, garlic, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Blend for 1 minute, or until sauce is smooth.
Add chopped parsley.
Pour over hot linguine and toss to coat well.
Serve topped with Blue cheese.
Serves four.

title: nut roll
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Let butter soften and mix with dry ingredients like pie dough.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Dough will be soft.
Put in a bowl, cover with Saran Wrap and put in refrigerator for 8 hours or overnight.
Take out of refrigerator and let set about 1 hour.
Divide dough into 3 parts.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo.
Cook over low heat until soft ball or use thermometer. Remove from heat. Add marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and vanilla. Stir.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses; beat thoroughly.
Sift the dry ingredients; add to cream mixture, alternating with water and beating after each addition.
Bake in greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican import
directions: Saut beef until crumbly; drain off excess fat. Add onion, garlic salt, tomato sauce and olives to sauted beef. Combine sour cream, cottage cheese and chilies in separate bowl. Crush tortilla chips slightly; reserve several whole chips for garnish. Place 1/2 the crumbled chips in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole. Add meat mixture. Cover meat mixture with 1/2 the sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Repeat layers. Bake in moderate (350°) oven 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered, or until bubbly hot. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter and egg.
Press in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
(Do not use glass pan.)
Mix together next five ingredients.
Pour this in the pan.

title: hot corned beef spread
directions: Cream ingredients and chill.
Serve with rye bread or crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix dressing and butter with hands.
Pat 3/4 of mixture into bottom of baking pan.
Mix rest of the ingredients together and put on top of dressing mixture, except for the rest of the remaining dressing mixture.
Put this on top of soup and chicken mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jan hagels
directions: Line 9 x 13 pan with foil, grease.
In medium-sized bowl, mix flour, 1/4 c. sugar, cinnamon, and butter with fingertips until crumbly. Mix in egg yolk until evenly blended.
Press into pan. Brush beaten egg white evenly onto mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 c. sugar and the almonds over top, pressing nuts lightly into batter.
Bake at 350° for 18-20 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool slightly.
Lift foil and cookie mix onto cutting board.
Cut into squares.
Cool completely.
Store these Dutch cookies for several days for flavor to blend.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.

title: lasagna
directions: In saucepan, combine tomato juice, vinegar, sweetener and garlic salt. Cook over moderate heat 40 minutes or until mixture is reduced by half. Let stand 10 minutes. In baking dish, alternate layers of lasagna noodles, tomato sauce, cheese, spinach, oregano and red peppers. Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Cook beans until almost done.
Brown onion and garlic in salad oil.
Add meat and brown.
Add to beans.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 15 minutes or until done.
Yields 10 to 15 servings.

title: potato and green onion ravioli with tomatoes and thyme
directions: Cook potatoes in large pot of boiling water until tender; drain.
Transfer to bowl and mash.
Blend in cheese and egg.
Thin potato mixture slightly with milk if very dry.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix in onions.
Place 1 heaping teaspoonful potato mixture in center of wrapper.
Brush edges with water.
Fold wrappers in half; press edges to release air bubbles and seal, forming half circle.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
(Can be made 2 days ahead.
Place in single layer on waxed paper-lined cookie sheets and freeze.
Do not thaw before cooking.)
Cook ravioli in batches in large pot of boiling, salted water until just tender, about 2 minutes for fresh, 5 minutes for frozen.
Transfer to plates using slotted spoon.
Tent with foil to keep warm. Meanwhile, melt butter in heavy small skillet over medium heat. Mix in thyme.
Spoon over ravioli.
Garnish with tomatoes and serve.

title: fruit punch
directions: I make an ice block with ginger ale the day before.

title: raspberry pie(won best pie award crievewood baptist, 1977)
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add frozen berries and lemon juice; stir until berries thaw.
Chill until partially set.
Blend cheese, confectioners sugar, vanilla and salt. Fold whipped cream, sweetened with 2 tablespoons sugar, into cheese mixture.

title: trout with tomatoes and herbs
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet over high heat.
Add garlic slices and saute until golden brown and then set aside.
Dry trout and stuff cavities with fresh herbs.
Tie trout with kitchen string. Saute fish in hot olive oil for 4 minutes on each side.
Reduce heat and add tomatoes, basil and reserved garlic.
Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook cabbage in water (small amount) about 6 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 10 minutes.
This is a Weight Watchers recipe.

title: carolina apple pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, apples, nutmeg, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Bake in 10-inch unbaked pastry shell 1 hour at 350°.

title: wrapped herb chicken(perfect for working moms with no time to cook!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place each chicken piece on large sheet of foil.
Top each with 1 tablespoon herbs, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, 1 teaspoon onion powder, 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon parsley.
Fold foil tightly around chicken, with double folds on each edge.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together cornmeal, flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and garlic salt.
Add onions.
Combine egg and buttermilk, then add to dry ingredients, stirring until mixture is moist.
Drop batter by teaspoonful into deep hot oil (400°), frying only a few at a time. Turn hush puppies once and cook until they are a golden brown. Remove and drain on brown paper towels.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Remove stems from mushrooms. Make small balls from sausage.
Place in mushroom cap.
Make well in the center of the sausage and pour a few drops of Worcestershire sauce and sprinkle a little garlic powder on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until nice and brown.

title: punch
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and just before serving, add strawberry pop and carbonated water or club soda.
Serves 22 to 25 (5 ounce) servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Drain. Stir in sauce, seasoning and veggies.
In bowl, mix parsley, Ricotta cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and 2 cups of Mozzarella. Begin layering, start with meat sauce, then noodles and then cheese mixture in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
You should end with noodles on top.
Take remaining Mozzarella and top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes; uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes until cheese is bubbly and browning. Let set 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir onion and mushrooms in 1 tablespoon margarine in 10-inch skillet until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in milk, soup and reserved mushroom liquid.
Stir in chicken.
Heat until hot.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter. In a mixing bowl combine powdered sugar and graham crackers. Mix well, then pour butter mixture over cracker mixture. Mix well. Press all into a 9x13 pan. For topping melt chocolate chips and spread over bars.

title: philadelphia scrapple
directions: Cook pork in water until tender.
Remove meat and let broth cool; skim off fat.
Grind meat and return to broth.
Add seasonings and return to a boil.
Combine flour and cornmeal; slowly add to cooking mixture, stirring constantly.
Boil for one hour, stirring often.
Pour into loaf pans and let cool.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set in middle.

title: beef stir fry
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a glass casserole dish. Cover and bake at 400 degrees for about 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook
and
mash
potatoes, then measure.
Add remaining ingredients
all
at
once and mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then reduce to 350° until pie is set.

title: sausage and egg brunch
directions: Place bread pieces on bottom of a buttered 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole.
Place sausages on top of bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Stir together eggs, milk and mustard; pour evenly over cheese.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife, inserted in center, comes out clean.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients into a large pot.
Cook until beef is tender.

title: marian's carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in pineapple, nuts, carrots and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix coconut, milk and water together.
Let stay in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, mix all ingredients together, pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream in small bowl.
Add seasoning and mix.
In large bowl, mix broccoli, onions and cheese.
Toss completely with mayonnaise mix.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Heat soup; drain broccoli.
Combine all and top with bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: golden cheese sauce
directions: Melt oleo and remove from heat.
Blend in flour and cook until thickened.
Combine yolks and lemon juice and mix with sauce. Heat 1 minute and stir in cheese.
Serve over cooked vegetables.

title: ham and cheese treats
directions: With electric knife or bread knife, slice bread in 2 parts. Layer ham and cheese. Put top of bread on top. Mix together all other ingredients and drizzle over top. Marinate overnight in the refrigerator. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Slice individually or 2 together for larger servings. Can be frozen but do not cook first. Set out 1/2 hour to thaw before baking if frozen.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir soda into applesauce until foaming.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour and spices; add to mixture.
Fold in candied fruit and walnuts.
Line loaf pans with brown paper, then wax paper.
Pour fruitcake mixture into 2 (12 x 3 1/2-inch) pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pans and immediately peel off wax paper.
Cool completely on racks.
Put in foil wrapping and place in freezer several days (or longer).
While still firm, slice as desired.

title: edwinia's pound cake
directions: Blend sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing well.
Add flour and cream alternately, mixing well.
Add vanilla and mix (the more you mix the better the cake).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soup and Cheez Whiz, mixing until well blended.
Add chicken and green chilies.
Spread 1/2 cup of chicken mixture over the bottom of a 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Layer four of the tortillas, dipping each in enchilada sauce, and one-third of the remaining chicken mixture. Repeat layers two more times.
Cover with foil; bake 20 minutes. Remove foil; continue baking 15 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: virginia's candy balls
directions: Melt together in double boiler.
Dip balls using toothpick as handle and replace on tray.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, white sugar and margarine. Add vanilla and eggs. Mix well. Add vanilla pudding, flour and soda. Mix well. Add as many chocolate chips as desired. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy. Add one egg at a time. Beat well after each.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cook wings in microwave for 20 minutes.
Blend liquid ingredients together.
Pour over wings.
Bake in 375° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bacon cheese potatoes
directions: Cut several small or medium potatoes in half.
Spoon out center of potato and bake at 325° to 350° until done.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese and bacon bits on top.
Bake for 5 minutes or until cheese starts to brown.

title: taco bake
directions: Mix Bisquick milk and beans; spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook and drain beef.
Add taco sauce.
Pour mixture on bean mixture. Top with cheese.
Bake about 20 minutes at 425°.
Serve topped with crushed corn chips, sour cream, shredded lettuce and tomatoes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, drain.
Slice cheese.
Place broccoli in buttered baking dish.
Place cheese slices on top. Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Melt butter and pour over.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cold deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in two lengthwise and remove yolks.
Chill the whites.
Cream yolks with ingredients.
Roll into balls and replace in each half egg white.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop chicken; add onion, cheese, chicken noodle soup, cream of mushroom soup, Rice-A-Roni plus seasoning packet in rice and 1/2 cup broth.
Mix well.
Pour in casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Top with can of onion rings (optional).

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar until light colored and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and eggs.
Set aside.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda, ginger, cloves and cinnamon.
Gradually mix flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Roll dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Dip tops into granulated sugar.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans; set aside.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
After comes to a full boil, remove from heat and add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper or pour into pan and cut into squares.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Mix until mealy.
Press into bottom of greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Spread jam on cooled crust.
Sprinkle nuts over jam.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Apricot jam is a good alternative.

title: pepperoni chicken rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350 to 375 degrees.
Take chicken breasts and pound with mallet until tender.
Season chicken to taste with garlic powder, salt, pepper and Italian style seasoning.
Place about 5 slices of pepperoni on top of chicken breasts and then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up chicken breasts and pin with toothpicks.

title: raspberry-orange slush
directions: Combine raspberries and orange juice in container of an electric blender; cover and process until smooth.
Strain mixture and discard seeds.
Combine raspberry mixture and 1/2 cup carbonated beverage in an 8-inch square baking pan.
Cover and freeze 3 hours or until slushy.

title: peanut butter brickle
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Cover with crackers. Boil butter and sugar 2 minutes and pour over crackers.
Sprinkle with both chips.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, salt and baking soda; stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by tablespoons on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Bring raisins, water, orange juice and marmalade to a boil. Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and cloves together.
Gradually add some of the boiling mixture to the cornstarch mixture to make a liquid.
Then stir this liquid mixture into the boiling mixture gradually and cook until thick and clear.
Makes 3 cups.
Great served on baked ham.

title: peanut butter, chocolate, oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the following:
peanut butter, butter or margarine, brown sugar, granulated sugar, vanilla and baking soda.
Add eggs, then blend in oatmeal and milk chocolate chips.
Bake at 325` for 10 minutes.
Cookies will remain soft.

title: curried beef
directions: In electric wok, add oil.
Set control dial at 350°.
When light goes out, add steak, onion and curry powder; stir-fry until steak is browned on all sides, about 3 minutes.
Add water, soy sauce, cornstarch and sugar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils 1 minute.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: heavenly dip
directions: Mix ingredients and blend together with a wooden spoon, using a "folding" action.
Place in refrigerator in a covered container for at least 1/2 hour.
Will keep a week in the refrigerator. Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.
Sweet red pepper flakes add color and a different flavor.
This is also tasty as a sauce for hot vegetables such as broccoli or as a topping for baked potatoes.
Allow to come to room temperature before topping hot vegetables.
Yield: approximately 20 ounces.

title: party chicken
directions: Roll chicken breasts, wrap in bacon and secure with toothpick. Cover bottom of baking dish with ham and arrange chicken.
Cover with soup and sour cream mixture.
Bake at 325° 1 1/2 hours.

title: rich fruit salad
directions: Add lemon juice to Eagle Brand milk.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan; cover and cook over very low heat, about 30 minutes or until rice is tender and milk has been absorbed.
Stir occasionally.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and gradually stir about 1/4 of hot rice mixture into yolk mixture.
Add yolk mixture to remaining rice mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until boiling. Remove from heat.

title: listy
directions: Mix flour and margarine until crumbly, then mix sour cream, egg yolks and vanilla together.
Add to flour and margarine.
Mix well.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Divide into 4's and roll out thin on floured board.
Cut in 4-inch squares.
Make a
slit in middle.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together milk, eggs and corn.
Add chopped peppers, sugar and cornmeal mix.
Stir well and pour into hot, greased skillet. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cherry sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar, butter, eggs and pineapple with butter.
Add bread cubes and mix.
Use milk to moisten.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cordon bleu rice
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine rice, ham, cheese, parsley and butter in medium bowl.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes.
Yield: 5 cups.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Cut each squash into halves; remove seeds and fibers.
Pare squash.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: green chile pork and beans
directions: Brown pork roast in combination of bacon fat and oil in Dutch oven.
Add 1 onion, chunked, and brown this, too.
Salt and pepper entire roast and cover partially with water.
Cover with lid and cook until meat is tender.

title: salted peanut crunchies
directions: Cream together margarine, peanut butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift together 2 cups flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed ingredients.
Then add chocolate chips and Spanish peanuts.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges barely look brown at 350°.
Can omit peanuts and use crunchy peanut butter.
Freezes great!

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream sugar and cheese together.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread on top of pretzel crust.
Very carefully, pour Jell-O mixture over this. Refrigerate.
(Can be made the day before using or early on same day to be used.)

title: pineapple dish
directions: Mix flour,
sugar and cheese in a bowl.
Into a greased casserole dish,
put
a
layer
of
pineapple, then sprinkle a layer of
the
cheese
mixture
over
the top.
Repeat layers. Pour reserved juice
over top.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 or 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Great with ham!

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in ungreased jelly roll pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and frost.
Let stand 1 hour before cutting.

title: company carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until done.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid to mix with next 3 ingredients.
Melt margarine and stir in crumbs.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla and mix in. Sift together and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and add chips, nuts, corn flakes and oatmeal.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen crunchy chocolate chip cookies.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together the margarine, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla. Add the eggs.
Add the peanut butter.
Mix together the salt, soda and oatmeal.
Add to other mixture.
Add M&M's and chocolate chips. Form into balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
One half batch.

title: honey mustard grilled chicken
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together dressing, mustard, juice, honey, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and turn to coat well; cover and marinate in refrigerator 1 hour or overnight.
Remove chicken from marinade and place on prepared grill about 6 inches from heat. Grill chicken, turning occasionally, about 35 minutes or until fork can be inserted with ease.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Melt oil in Dutch oven.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper. Saute, stirring often, until vegetables are tender.
Add ham and sausages and cook for a few minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Cover and bake for about 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender.
Serves 4.

title: strawberries with hot chocolate dipping sauce
directions: Break the chocolate into pieces and put them into a medium-sized heat-proof glass bowl.
Pour the cream into the bowl and spoon in the honey.
Only need a few drops of vanilla extract so you pour them gently and carefully into a teaspoon and stir this into the bowl.
Use your microwave oven to melt the sauce. Put the bowl uncovered into the oven and switch it full power for a few minutes.
Take bowl out; stir if it is lumpy.
Put in again on one.
Take it out.
Stir; let it cool, then you can eat it.

title: fruit snow
directions: In 2 quart nonmetal container, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover; freeze.
Scoop frozen mixture into dessert dishes. Makes 14 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Melt the butter in pan.
Add the first 5 ingredients.
Mix the Bisquick, milk and egg.
Pour over ingredients. Cook approximately 45 minutes at 400°.

title: bing cherry ring
directions: Drain cherries; save juice.
Remove pits.
Make jello with 2 cups of hot water; let cool.
Add cherry juice which is usually 1 cup or add enough water to make 1 cup.
Then, add 1 cup of wine, cherries and nuts.
Put in mold.
Fill center with cheese balls when serving.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and chill overnight.
Bake cake as directed and cut layers in half.
Cover with icing.
Keep cool.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix crab meat and Tobasco sauce and part of cheese with cream cheese.
Top with remaining cheese and bake until bubbly.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Rinse and sort.
Add beans and 2 quarts of water.
Combine all ingredients and cook covered on low for approximately 2 hours or until beans are soft.
To thicken, mash some beans or add a mixture of cornstarch and water.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cereal crisps
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until very thick.
Beat in sugar until mixed well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until dough is stiff, about 15 minutes.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients like crumbs, then add milk.
Beat together.
Pour batter over sliced fruit, which was placed in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup sugar over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and cake tests done.

title: bulgarian rice pudding(sootlash)
directions: Cover and cook the rice at low heat in 1 1/2 cups of water until the water evaporates, about 15-20 minutes.
Put the milk and cooked rice in a sauce pan.
Boil and reduce heat to a simmer. Put the cornstarch in a bowl.
Slowly add 3/4 cup of water, stirring constantly to make a smooth paste.
Add it to the simmering milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook for 10 minutes while stirring.
Add the sugar and cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Serve in individual bowls and cook in the refrigerator.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix well with fork.
Form into balls and place in baking dish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn occasionally.

title: betty's chicken
directions: Arrange broccoli stalks in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in 9 x 12 dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: In the bottom of a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish, place uncooked rice.
Place pork chops on top of rice.
Pour soup and water over rice and pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Pour boiling water over ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.
Will be nice and thick.
One and one-third of this mixture is equal to one can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain.
Mix in flour.
Grate in Longhorn cheese.
Add milk, Worcestershire sauce and eggs.
Can also add onions, green chilies or lemon pepper.
Put meat mixture in pie shell and bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until it bubbles and browns.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix milk and water.
Add sugar and mix until smooth.

title: irresistible brownies
