title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Place short ribs in large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over ribs. Cover and refrigerate 8 to 10 hours. Turn occasionally. Remove from marinade and drain. Cook slowly on grill 7 to 8-inches from coals, 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat begins to leave bone. Turn often. Brush with marinade during last 20 minutes of cooking. Serves 4 to 6.

title: birish
directions: Peel and slice apples; set aside.
Cook potatoes and rice while hot.
Add flour and salt; mix.
Roll out the size of a pie crust.
Cover with apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat together.
Beat in 1 pint vanilla ice cream.
Pour in shell.
Sprinkle coconut on top and refrigerate.

title: crisp vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef; drain and save bouillon.
In large pan, combine beef, tomato juice, beef bouillon, onion, celery and corn.
Season to taste.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes.
Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with cheese.

title: quick key lime pie
directions: Mix together lime juice and milk.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
Will keep up to several weeks frozen.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Make the day before.
Cream all ingredients.
Cut shrimp in small pieces.
Serve on American Harvest crackers or Sociables.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix orange candy with 1/4 cup flour.
Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat thoroughly. Beat in sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in rolled oats and candy. Drop from a teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes or until delicately browned.
Yields 90 cookies.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, place apples at the bottom.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: easy cajun catfish
directions: Heat
broiler.	Melt butter and combine with spices and salt. Coat
fish	fillets
with
mixture.
Broil until opaque throughout, about 5 minutes per side.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Add salt and pepper to flour.
Dredge chicken pieces.
Brown in heavy pan turning several times.
Add garlic, bouquet garni, wine, brandy and tomatoes.
Cover pan tightly.
Cook over low heat about 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Taste for seasoning at 30 minutes and add mushrooms.
Add parsley when done.
Serve with chunks of French bread to dip in sauce.
Serves 10 to 12. This may be prepared ahead and improves with reheating.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in a large pot, cover with water and cook until tender. Pull chicken from bone, discard bones and skin. Strain broth.
Put broth in the same pot, adding enough canned chicken broth to make 2 qt. Heat to boiling.
Add 1/2 stick margarine.

title: millionaire cheesecake ronile
directions: Use a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Butter sides and bottom heavily.
Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter or margarine.
Press firmly over bottom and about 2 1/2 inches up sides.
Chill the crust-lined pan in the refrigerator.

title: condensed milk(same as eagle brand)
directions: Mix sugar and water in boiler and simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool.
Place all ingredients in blender and process until smooth.
Keeps several days in fridge, longer in freezer.
Double recipe for larger amount since most recipes call for 14 ounces.

title: sheath cake recipe
directions: Bring to boil oleo, shortening, cocoa and water.
Sift together in bowl, flour and sugar.
Add to bowl, buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, soda and cinnamon.
Add chocolate mixture to flour mixture and mix well by hand.
Pour cake mixture into pan and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: spicy chicken
directions: 1. In a large sauce pan lightly simmer all ingredients except chicken, lemon juice, and cayenne/tabasco.
Simmer until all ingredients are mixed. 2. Remove mixture from heat and add lemon juice.
Place chicken in large baking dish and pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 2-7 hours. 3. To bake heat oven at 350°, cooking & basting chicken 20 -30 minutes.
Add cayenne or tabasco about 10-15 minutes before chicken is done.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake at 350° for thirty minutes. This is a wonderful dish for your Thanksgiving or Christmas dinner.
Enjoy!

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Cook on low heat for 2 minutes. Add milk and stir until it boils.
Remove from heat; add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Pour on cake while still hot. Goes really well with Duncan Hines spice cake.

title: blush sauce
directions: Put all the ingredients except the heavy cream in a saucepan and cook at the merest simmer for 1 hour, uncovered.
Stir from time to time with a wooden spoon.
Puree the contents of the pan through a food mill into a saucepan and bring to a simmer, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Add the heavy cream and stir.
Cook for 1 minute more.
Taste and correct for salt.
Serve immediately over pasta.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add oil and eggs; mix well.
Add carrots and walnuts. Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake one hour in 325° oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Slowly add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Use a fork dipped in flour and make a crisscross design on balls.
Sprinkle with sugar if desired.
Bake for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chile casserole
directions: Put in layers, cheese on top.
Cook in oven for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pie crust
directions: In large bowl, cut shortening into flour and salt with pastry cutter.
Mixture should look like corn meal.
Add just enough water to form a ball.
Roll onto floured surface to desired shape. Place into pie pan.
Makes double crust for 8 or 9-inch pie.

title: macon's dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together with whisk.
Store in a jar in the refrigerator.
Especially good over green salad.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine meat, crumbs, milk, onion, Parmesan cheese, eggs and seasoning.
Mix lightly.
Press meat mixture into an 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes. Pour out drippings.
Spread pizza sauce over meat and bake for 10 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: green chile cheese dip
directions: Add chilies, sour cream and onion to cream cheese and beat with mixer until well blended.
(If necessary, add milk or half and half to get correct dipping consistency.)
Cover and refrigerate for several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crisp tortilla chips.

title: enid's orange bran muffins
directions: Mix bran and orange juice together and set aside.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. In a large bowl, cream honey and shortening.
Add egg and beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and bran/orange juice mixture.
Do not overmix.
Add crushed pineapple.
Spoon mixture into greased muffin tins and bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hot chinese chicken
directions: Roll chicken pieces in cornstarch.
Heat oil in frypan or wok over high heat. Add chicken quickly to brown. Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Add tomato, mushrooms, onions and celery. Stir. Sprinkle with Accent.
Add soy sauce. Cover and reduce heat to simmer for 5 minutes.
Put over lettuce and rice.

title: broccoli and corn
directions: Melt butter; add dressing mix and mix other ingredients.
Put half of dressing in greased casserole.
Add other ingredients. Put other half of dressing mix on top.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch Corning Ware 40 minutes at 350°.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl.
Make a hollow in center of flour mixture and add egg. Add 1 tablespoon water, then gradually fold in flour mixture.
Let stand for one hour.
Put marble size knob of Crisco into each section of muffin tin.
Place in hot oven until the Crisco is smoking.
Add mixture into tin.
Cook at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: special broccoli
directions: Wash and separate broccoli to florets (can use stalks if peeled, cut into 1-inch cubes).
Bring water and bouillon cubes or chicken broth to boil.
Boil until reduced by 1/3.
Add broccoli. Cook until tender-crisp or to your preference.
Drain, reserving liquid, if desired to cook rice and noodles.
This is the only way I cook broccoli or any raw vegetable.

title: mandarin cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together thoroughly.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: egg hero
directions: Split bread loaf in half lengthwise.
On bottom half, layer the lettuce, carrots, egg slices, tomatoes and cucumber.
Top with another layer of egg slices.
Pour salad dressing of choice over egg slices. Cover with top half of the loaf. Cut in 2-inch pieces. Serve.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: tasty prunes
directions: Put 1 teaspoon of cream cheese in center of prune.
Place a chunk of pineapple on top of cream cheese.

title: pralines
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, to 236° or to soft ball stage.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Beat until creamy, but still soft.
Drop in mounds on wax paper.

title: sugar and spice nuts
directions: Mix all together with spatula.
Pour into a greased broiler pan.
Bake at 275° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Stir a couple of times when cooking to break loose with spatula.
When done, pour onto waxed paper.

title: texas ranch casserole
directions: Combine soups.
Add Ro-Tel and chicken broth.
Arrange alternately layers of tortillas, chicken, onion, sauce and cheese in baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: italian beef
directions: Place beef in roaster half full of water. Add salt and onions. Roast until tender. Remove from oven and refrigerate overnight.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together dry cake mix, melted margarine and 3 eggs. Spread in the bottom of a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and melted margarine; spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cool, sift powdered sugar on top. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sugar-free peach pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine Jell-O, pudding and water.
Cook until boiling.
Cool (will thicken as it cools).
Add peaches and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: meat pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with one nine-inch pie crust.
Layer first with meat, then potatoes, carrots and onions.
Season to taste.
Repeat the layer again.
If using a deep-dish pie plate, you may be able to get three layers.
On top of the last layer, top with 1 stick of margarine sliced and placed all over the top (sometimes I don't use a whole stick).
Then top with the other 9-inch pie crust; flute edges and cut slits in top of the crust. Place on cookie sheet and bake in oven for 2 hours at 200°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain; melt oleo and add onions, flour, cheese, milk and soup.
Mix well and heat over low heat until cheese is melted.
Mix in broccoli and pour mixture into lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, jello, oil, nectar or juice, extract and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350° in a tube or Bundt pan.
Grease and flour pan.

title: pepper chicken
directions: In large saucepan, med. heat, combine sliced green pepper and sliced onions.
Simmer until slightly soft in water.
Add garlic powder and seasoning salt (as desired) to pan.
Take out, put in bowl.
Leaving water in pan, add chicken to pan.
Cook until done. Take out and dice chicken.
Add chicken, pepper and onions back into saucepan with can of chicken flavored gravy.
Let simmer 2-3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Cook diced potatoes 8 to 12 minutes until tender when pierced. Drain and cool.
Layer into a covered container: potatoes, celery, onions and parsley.
Salt and pepper and follow the layers as began.
Put lid on container and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and mix with potato mixture.
Place in serving bowl.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Garnish with parsley.
Cover and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: frosted apricot bars
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon, oil and flour.
Mix well.
Add apricots and fold into mixture.
Pour on a well greased 11 x 15 inch cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Cool.

title: green beans au jambon julienne
directions: Prepare beans, add to boiling salted water.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain beans.
Cut ham 2-inches long and 1/4-inch wide. Saute onions in butter, 5 minutes; add ham and cook 2 minute or less.
Add remaining ingredients and mix all with beans.
Stir gently to mix.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Cream together the egg, sugar, butter and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Slice bread in strips, dip in batter and bake or deep fry.
Makes 4.

title: nacho dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer all ingredients in the order listed in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: chicken primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil and margarine.
Add onion and garlic and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms, broccoli, zucchini and carrot and cook 3 more minutes.
Add wine, basil, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Toss pasta and chicken with vegetables.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: simple tomato sauce
directions: Lightly brown cut up onion and/or mushrooms in olive oil.
Add both cans of tomatoes.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Cook for about an hour.

title: no bake icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers into fine crumbs.
Mix first 7 ingredients together, then add Eagle Brand milk.
Make sure ingredients are well mixed.
Use 1 large tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Line pans with wax paper or plastic wrap.
Press firmly into lined pans.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Let
cheese
be at room temperature.
Blend in mayo and sugar. Add
fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla.
Pour into
a
large
rectangular pan.
Freeze at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; beat well.
Bake in 3 layers at 325° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on box.
Drain and cool.
Add other ingredients (diced).
Mix and chill.

title: fresh broccoli chowder
directions: Place 2 cups of broth in large saucepan. Add broccoli and bring to a boil.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes until tender. Add milk, cream, cheese, ham and butter.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: spiced blueberry jam
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Remove from fire and add pectin.
Skim and pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Combine peaches (drained if canned) and remaining 1 cup sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over batter.
Do not stir. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: fruit dip
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Mix by hand or with mixer (low speed) until well blended and smooth.
Serve with several types of cut up fresh fruit.

title: crab meat cocktail
directions: Remove bony tissue.
Combine with 1 cup finely chopped celery. Chill and serve on lettuce lined cocktail cups with cocktail sauce.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Toss together celery, green onions, rice and chicken.
Mix sugar, salt, salad oil, vinegar and pepper to make a dressing. Toss dressing with chicken mixture and refrigerate.
Add torn lettuce when ready to serve.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Filling:
Mix the sugar and cream cheese.

title: never fail icing
directions: Mix together
all ingredients, except vanilla and nuts. Let mixture cook
minutes
after
it
starts to boil.
Cool slightly.
Add vanilla
and
beat (add nuts).
You need to let it cool, beating it
while it is cooling.
It will not firm up or run off cake, if not cooled down.

title: peach or cherry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place butter or margarine in baking dish (approximately 8 x 8-inch).
Place in oven to melt.
Mix together the first 5 ingredients; pour into melted butter.
Place peaches or cherries on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or milk on top.

title: carrots marinade
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in blender or by hand.
Cut carrots in small pieces and parboil.
After first 6 ingredients have been well blended, add the carrots.
Sliver onion and green pepper and add to the mixture.
Put mixture in bowl and refrigerate overnight or until needed.

title: dunked cookies
directions: Spread small amount of Cool Whip in dish.
Dunk cookies in milk and layer on Cool Whip.
Repeat layers 1 to 2 more times. Refrigerate several hours.

title: banana punch
directions: Be careful in your selection.

Do not chooose too young and take only such varieties as have been reared in a good atmosphere. When once selected, let that part remain forever settled and give your entire attention to preparation for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others are constantly getting them in hot water.

This only makes them sour, hard and bitter. Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste, wrapped in love and warmed in devotion.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years and improve with age.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, steak sauce, Tabasco sauce, garlic powder and parsley.
Form it into a ball and roll in nuts.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Serve with crackers.
(If you prefer, can roll back in the parsley, instead of the nuts.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk.
Cook over medium heat stirring until thoroughly mixed and sugar is dissolved.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes after mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cook and cut into squares.

title: chicken dish
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone and chop into pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients and add chicken.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and crumble Ritz crackers on top (enough to cover).
Bake for 5 more minutes or until brown.

title: classic chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs, gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie pan.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 9 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; cook broccoli.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery until soft.
In a large bowl, combine rice, broccoli and vegetables.
Add soup and cheese; mix well.
Place in uncovered casserole at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Congeal jello and whip cream cheese with pineapple juice and 1/2 cup nuts.
Stir into jello mixture.
Mix and store in icebox.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook the sweet potatoes.
Peel the apples and cut in quarters.
Slice the potatoes and put half in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Add half of the apples, brown sugar and butter.
Add remaining potatoes.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple-pecan cake
directions: Mix
all
dry
ingredients including apples and pecans. Mix all liquids together (Wesson oil, eggs and vanilla).
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease and flour large baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: spiced applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth; add egg and beat well. Stir in applesauce.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda, spices and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add raisins and nuts.
Turn batter into a well-greased, lightly floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 375° until pick inserted in middle comes out clean, usually about 45 minutes.
Let cake rest in pan until almost cool, then turn out on plate.

title: pineapple ambrosia salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Blend reserved juice with sour cream.
Combine with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.

title: no stir peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in deep baking dish and in a 350° oven to melt. Make batter of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour mixture over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Empty can of peaches on top.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large salad bowl, mix finely chopped broccoli, diced green onions, chopped nuts, raisins and cooked and crumbled bacon.

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add food coloring and peanuts.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often.
Cook until no syrup is left. Pour into flat pan or cookie sheet and spread out.
Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Combine ingredients until creamy.
Using teaspoon, shape into balls.
Put on cookie sheet about an inch apart.
Flatten with palm of hand.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian pea salad
directions: Cube the Mozzarella.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan, then stir in Bisquick, sugar and milk. Add fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix and pour all ingredients into deep dish pie crust.
Top with a regular pie crust, leaving pan on.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove top pan; bake for 15 more minutes, or until golden brown.

title: cherry-sherry
directions: Early in day:
Drain cherries, reserving liquid.
To liquid, add enough water to make 1 3/4 cups.
In medium saucepan over high heat, heat liquid to boiling.
Place gelatin in medium bowl; stir in liquid until gelatin is dissolved.
Add cherries, sherry and almonds.
Refrigerate.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine beef and onion in skillet.
Cook until beef is lightly brown.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese over beef mixture.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O into hot water.
Add cold water.
Add fruit and marshmallows, chill until congealed.
Cook next four ingredients until thick and allow to cool.
Spread the cooled mixture over Jell-O mixture. Whip the whipping cream and blend cream cheese.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top and chill.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and 1 cup nectar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Put everything in a slow cooker.

title: crab and shrimp nachos
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil to a depth of one-half inch.
Cut the tortillas in quarters and fry each piece for a few seconds or until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.

title: squaw valley banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine biscuit mix, brown sugar, soda and nutmeg in a small mixing bowl.
Beat together the bananas, oil and eggs until well blended.
Stir into dry ingredients all at once, mixing only until blended.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
Place in an 8-inch microproof dish.
Add garlic and butter (butter cut in pieces).
Cover with waxed paper and cook on 90 (Saute) for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once after 2 minutes.
(Serve with roast beef or steak, or as a surprise side dish with any meal.)
Easy and quick!!

title: orange fluff
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: walk-to-school cookies
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Form into marble size balls and place on a cookie sheet. Mash balls flat with bottom of a small glass or fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 11 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream cheese and margarine.
Add dry ingredients; mix well. Pack into cookie press.
Press onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Transfer to wire racks to cool (or you can serve warm).

title: raspberry cream cheese delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom and sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cook chicken.
Place open muffins in a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Slice or pull chicken apart and cover the muffins with cooked chicken.

title: spicy sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; blend in egg, honey, sour milk and vanilla; beat.
Sift the dry ingredients, add and mix well. Form into small balls, dip into milk and then in sugar.
Bake.

title: chicken dish
directions: Stew fryers for 1 hour, seasoned to taste with chopped onion, oregano, salt, pepper, sweet basil and bay leaf.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
In a small skillet, melt margarine.
Add green pepper and onion; saute until crisp-tender.
In a large bowl, combine cream-style corn, whole corn, eggs and corn muffin mix.
Blend well.
Add onion mixture; mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind up Oreo cookies and set aside to dry.
Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Set side.
Mix vanilla pudding mixture with milk.
Set aside until it sets.
Mix cheese mixture with pudding mixture, then mix in Cool Whip.

title: chocolate-marble muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chopped almonds, reserving some for garnish.
Combine egg, orange juice and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients until mixed.
Remove half of batter; stir in cocoa and set aside.
To remaining batter, stir in orange peel.
Place paper liners in standard-size 12-muffin pan. Holding pan tipped slightly to side, spoon orange batter into one side of muffin liner.
Fill other side of liners with chocolate batter.
Sprinkle with reserved almonds.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: peanut butter strips
directions: Cut crust from bread, cut each slice into three strips.
Place on a cookie sheet, on another sheet place crust.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Place crust on newspaper.
Roll with rolling pin until fine crumbs.
Add parsley flakes and red pepper flakes to taste and mix well.

title: peanut butter pie ii
directions: Mix peanut butter and
powdered
sugar.
Make
a
crumb mixture; reserve a small amount for
garnish.
Sprinkle crumbs on crust.
Make a vanilla pudding and pour over crust and crumb mixture while it is still hot.
Cool.
Top with whipped
topping (whipped
cream, Cool Whip) and garnish with reserved crumb mixture.
Chill.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, juice and water.
Freeze until ready to use.
Let thaw about 2 or 3 hours before using.
Stir with a spoon.
Add 1 quart ginger ale.

title: mexicali bake meatballs
directions: In oven-going skillet, blend cheese spread with milk over low heat.
Stir in enchilada sauce.
Add frozen meatballs, hominy and chilies. Bring to a boil.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with corn chips.
Transfer to oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: egg and ham casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread and tear into large pieces.
Layer ham and bread in greased casserole.
Mix other ingredients and pour over.
Cover and refrigerate overnight (or for 1 hour). Bake at 325° approximately 40 minutes until firm and puffy.
A sharp knife inserted should come out clean when done.
May add shredded cheese as a topping.

title: oven baked fries(serves 4)
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise into strips.
Cook, covered, in a microwave oven on High (100% power) for 5 minutes.
Allow to stand for at least 3 minutes or until cool enough to handle.
Arrange potato slices on baking sheet.
Spray with cooking oil and sprinkle with salt.
Bake uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°, until crisp and browned around edges.
(Thicker slices require up to 30 minutes.)
Serve hot.
Also good using unpeeled sweet potatoes.
Calories, 89; cholesterol, 0; sodium, 3 milligrams fat, 2 grams.

title: spanish green beans
directions: Saute
onions and pepper until tender.	Add flour; stir and add tomatoes, green beans, bacon, salt and pepper.	Place in a buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Take off heat.
Mix in flour, mustard and salt.
Put back on low heat.
Mix in milk.
Stir continually until it thickens.
Add in sharp Cheddar cheese.
Take off heat after cheese melts.
Cook elbows as directed on box.
Drain and pour into a 9 x 13 pan.
Add cream sauce.
Melt other 1/4 cup margarine and combine with bread crumbs.
Shred mild cheese and sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cranberry bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin. In separate bowl mix flour, spices, soda and salt.
Pour wet ingredients into well in center of dry mix. Add cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in two greased and floured loaf pans.

title: blintze souffle
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange frozen blintzes in 2 rows in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour mixture over blintzes.
Bake in 350° oven until fluffed and golden, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Cut and serve with low-fat sour cream or fruit topping.

title: squash soup
directions: Melt butter, add onion and cook on low heat until soft, not brown. Add squash and broth. Cook until squash is tender. Add sugar. Process until smooth (use hand-held processor or move to food processor). Add cream and seasonings. Serve hot or cold.

title: green-top tomatoes
directions: Mix spinach with remaining ingredients, except tomatoes.
Pile mixture on top of tomato slices.
Place on buttered baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: bran-raisin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom only of 12 to 18 medium muffin cups.
(Important for 4-H but at home I use just use Pam.) Mix cereal, raisins and water; let stand for 2 minutes.
Beat eggs in 2 1/2-quart bowl; stir in buttermilk, oil and cereal mixture. Stir in remaining ingredients all at once, just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.

title: fancy hamburgers
directions: Mix all together.
Best if let stand for a couple of hours in refrigerator.
Form into patties; cook on grill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit together. In saucepan, put pineapple juice (and mandarin juice, if needed), flour, egg and sugar. Whisk and cook over medium heat until thickened. Cool and then pour over fruit. You can experiment with any fruit in any combination or amount as long as you make enough dressing to coat it all.

title: angel roll
directions: Grease bottom of jelly roll pan.
Line with wax paper and grease again.
Prepare angel food cake batter as directed on package.
Turn 1/2 batter into pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Use rest of batter for cupcakes.
Cool.
Insert on towel dusted with confectioners sugar.
Remove wax paper. Roll in towel.
Unroll. Spread with Dream Whip, chopped nuts and cherries.
Roll again. Refrigerate.

title: golden lasagne
directions: Brown or boil chicken.
While noodles are boiling, chop chicken into bite size chunks.

title: polenta(cornmeal mush]
directions: Use 1 tablespoon butter to lightly grease walls of crock-pot. Add paprika and cayenne.
Turn to high setting while measuring remaining ingredients.
Add to crock-pot with remaining melted butter.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low setting for 6 to 9 hours (on high for 2 to 3 hours).

title: bean soup(quick kind)
directions: Put water and bouillon in pot. Stir to mix. Add beans, onion and carrot. Bring to boil. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, hamburger and macaroni.
Make two layers with hamburger mixture, cheese and pepperoni.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grammy's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with water to sugar mixture.
Add oatmeal, 1 cup fruit, too, if you want.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli with penne pasta *
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Three minutes before pasta is done, add broccoli to water.
Drain.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add mashed bananas.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted flour and baking soda. Add chopped nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cranberry-orange pineapple relish
directions: Grind oranges with cranberries.
Save juice.
Add sugar and pineapple with juice.
Add sugar and mix well.
Put in jars in refrigerator.

title: vern's coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for four minutes, stir in coconut and nuts.	Pour in bundt type pan, bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then remove and allow to finish cooling.
Frost with cream cheese frosting (see frostings).

title: strawberry apple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 8-inch round cake pan.
Arrange overlapping apple slices in circle to cover bottom of pan.
Melt brown sugar and margarine together.
Pour brown sugar mixture over apples.
Combine muffin mix and milk in bowl; stir until moistened. Pour evenly over apples.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately invert onto plate and serve.

title: asparagus cheese bake
directions: Cook asparagus as directed.
Cut 9 (2-inch) circles from bread slices.
Tear remaining bread into small pieces and place into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer asparagus, cheese and onion on bread pieces.
Top with bread circles.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, mustard and red pepper and pour on bread circles.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, until center is set, 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
(Will hold, covered, in refrigerator up to 24 hours before baking.)

title: old-fashioned creamy eggnog
directions: In 5-cup blender container, combine powdered sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Cover; blend at high speed until well blended (15 to 20 seconds).
In 2-quart saucepan, place 2 cups whipping cream.
Cook over medium heat until thermometer reaches 140° (5 to 6 minutes).
While blending at medium speed, slowly add warm whipping cream to egg mixture.
Continue blending until frothy (15 to 20 seconds).

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Brown country-style
spareribs.
Mix all ingredients of sauce. Pour over spareribs.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
(This sauce covers up to 8 ribs.)

title: frikadeller(danish meatballs)
directions: Combine beef and veal; add potatoes and onion.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and mix well.
Add egg, milk, salt and pepper and stir until well blended.
Shape into 30 balls using about 2 tablespoons of mixture for each ball.
Roll balls in remaining 1/3 cup flour. Fry in hot oil until brown.
Drain well.
Serve with stewed potatoes.

title: flan
directions: Put sugar in top of double boiler and caramelize, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Beat eggs.
Pour out milk and use can to measure.
Add 2 cans of hot water to the milk, vanilla and salt.
Add to eggs.
Add everything to caramelized sugar which should coat the sides and bottom of the pan.
Cook in double boiler for 45 minutes.
When done, the caramel is still around the sides of the custard and is like a sauce.

title: orange coconut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat by hand or with a rotary beater 4 or 5 minutes until thoroughly mixed and smooth.
Bake at 350° until done.
While warm, drizzle with Orange Glaze.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Combine chicken, soy sauce and garlic powder in a bowl; stir and set aside.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir and set aside. Heat oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add broccoli and next 4 ingredients; stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes or until tender crisp.
Remove vegetables from wok.
Add chicken mixture and stir-fry 5 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Return vegetables and stir in cornstarch mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and bay leaf with stock in a large pot. Cover and cook at medium heat for 20 minutes.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Stir over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not brown. Gradually blend in vegetable stock mixture.
Heat; do not boil. Before serving, add 2 to 3 ounces grated Velveeta cheese.
Do not freeze.

title: cherry bisque
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill evaporated milk at least 20 minutes.
Whip milk until doubled in size.
Add grated rind and juice of lemon to whipped milk.
Add canned pie filling. Crush 1 envelope graham crackers and sprinkle 3/4 of crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle top with rest of the crumbs.
Chill well.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: cranberry delight salad
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water until all berries pop open. While sauce is still hot, add jello and marshmallows.
Stir until they are dissolved and melted.
Cool.
Add apples, nuts and celery.
Stir well and refrigerate.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: In a medium pan with wooden spoon, stir together sugars and syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and cereal, stirring carefully. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Omit salt.
Drain and keep warm.
Place margarine in a large nonstick skillet.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add broccoli, carrots, onions, garlic and basil; saute 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add mushrooms, salt, pepper and wine and cook 2 minutes.
Gently toss pasta with vegetable mixture and cheese.
Yield:
9 servings; 146 calories per 3/4 cup serving and 4.2 fat.

title: how to preserve a happy home
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in the warmth of togetherness. Serve on a silver platter with smiles, hugs and kisses generously every day in large amounts.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Split angel food cake to make two layers.
Frost between layers, sides and top of cake. Put cherries on top of cake and refrigerate.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough onto cookie pan; press down firmly together in a large circle pizza shape.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spread tortilla chips in pan.
Pour meat mixture on top. Grate cheese over top.
Microwave until cheese melts.

title: caramelitas
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg, chocolate, milk and vanilla.
Mix in remaining ingredients on low speed to soft dough, scraping bowl constantly.
Halve the dough.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mold dough by rounded teaspoonfuls around caramel halves; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 minutes; cool. Blend remaining ingredients.
Swirl cookies in chocolate glaze.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and keep in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: smothered oxtails
directions: In a large mixing bowl pour flour; add salt and pepper to taste.
Batter oxtails.
In a large skillet, heat vegetable oil. Brown oxtails.
Place in baking dish with 2 to 3 cups of water. Add salt and pepper in water to your taste.
Quarter onion.
Add to oxtails.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Quarter potatoes; add to oxtails.
Cook 1 hour more until oxtails are good and tender.

title: ham and sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place balls about 2-inches apart in baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 7 dozen balls.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain off juice of beans and peas; set aside.
Add celery, pepper, onion and pimiento to beans and peas.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, paprika and water with juice of beans and peas.
Pour liquid mixture over vegetables; let set overnight.
Drain off liquid before serving.

title: country brunch casserole
directions: Saute sausage in skillet.
Drain grease.
Place half of cubed bread in 9-inch square pan.
Place half of sausage and half of cheese over bread.
Repeat layers.
Slightly beat eggs; add salt, mustard and milk.
Pour over bread-meat mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine the sour cream and milk in bowl.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Add pudding mix.
Beat for 2 minutes or until thickened and smooth.
Layer graham crackers and pudding (half at a time) in dish.
Top with pie filling.
Chill, covered, for 3 hours or longer.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: buttermilk salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over prepared salad. Tastes good with raw cauliflower and bacon bits in salad.

title: sweet cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add sugars, beat until combined. Stir in chocolate chips.
Cover and refrigerate for two hours.
Place on plastic wrap and shape into a ball.
Refrigerate for at least one hour. Roll in pecans before serving.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
In large bowl, combine 1 tablespoon sugar, shortening, salt and boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast mixture.
Stir in 3 to 4 cups flour; knead for 10 minutes.
Divide in half.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; store in closed container.
To make 1 batch, mix 6 tablespoons of dry mix to 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water.
Put in popsicle molds. Delicious.

title: tomato soup
directions: Mix butter, sugar, salt
and
flour.
Add
a little hot juice to mixture and mix
until
smooth, then mix with rest of juice. Boil 1/2 hour and put in jars.
Boil in hot water bath for 30 minutes.
Add
pint
milk
before serving.
Makes 10 pints.

title: olive filled cheese balls
directions: Cream the cheese
and
butter well.
Blend in flour and cayenne pepper.
If dough
is
too dry, add 2 teaspoons water. Make a ball.
Wrap about 1 teaspoon of dough around each olive to cover completely.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(May be placed on cookie sheet and frozen for later use.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture, then add pecans and apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash supreme
directions: Cook and drain squash; mash.
Add soup, cream, carrots and seasoning.
Butter casserole; sprinkle layer of Pepperidge Farm herb seasoning crumbs on bottom; add squash mixture.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and whisk or stir together.
Serve with raw cup up vegetables.
(Better if made the day before and refrigerated until ready to use.)

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add egg yolks and flour. Fold in peaches.

title: refreshing tuna-mac salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together all ingredients as given. Cover and chill
4 hours or overnight. Serves 6.

title: dieters (good) green beans
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat to simmer (low boil) for approximately 15 minutes.
Do not drain beans.

title: prize laundry soap
directions: Dissolve lye in 2 quarts of water.
Add grease or tallow.
It is important that the grease and lye are just warm, not hot, and that the grease is poured slowly into the lye.
Stir slowly for 10 to 15 minutes.
Then bring to boiling point and let boil 5 minutes.
Remove from fire and stir in powdered Borax.
Set aside and stir occasionally until the mixture begins to cool.
Then add liquid ammonia.
Stir round and round, slowly and evenly, until it is the consistency of cake batter.
Then turn into a mold and permit it to cool in the kettle.

title: orange-flavored eggnog
directions: In mixing bowl, combine vanilla ice cream, orange juice concentrate and egg; beat with electric or rotary beater. Gradually add milk, beating constantly.
Pour into chilled mugs; sprinkle with ground nutmeg.
Serves 6.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix oil, butter and all seasonings.
Heat slightly and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 225° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Serve warm or store in airtight container.

title: chicken pie deluxe
directions: Mix stuffing mix and melted butter.
Press 1/2 mixture in the bottom of casserole and save 1/2 to sprinkle over top.
Layer ingredients in casserole.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture. If casserole seems too dry, extra milk can be added.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: split pea potato soup
directions: In large, heavy pan, melt oleo.
Add onion; cook until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in beef broth and water; bring to a boil. Add the peas and potatoes.
Heat so that the mixture bubbles gently.
Cover; cook for 30 minutes, or until peas and potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat; cool 10 minutes.
In an electric blender or food processor, puree the soup in 5 batches, whirling each batch about 15 seconds.
Return to the pan over low heat; bring to serving temperature, stirring often.
Serves 4.

title: mock coconut custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend full 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mrs. ida lady's lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs and
add
sugar,
flour and lemon.
Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water and boil until thick.
Remove from the fire and add butter the size of a walnut.
This makes one pie.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all filling ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie crust. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake an additional 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish
with whipped cream, if desired.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix soda with applesauce; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add applesauce mixture and remaining dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add nuts; bake in greased and floured angel food cake pan for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add next 4 ingredients, stirring until onion and bell pepper are tender.
Add next 3 ingredients; stir until bubbly.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Sprinkle crumbled chips on top.
Stir to moisten chips.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven, uncovered, for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all other ingredients together and add spinach to mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in salad bowl.
Mix onion, pepper and celery. Layer over lettuce.
Add bacon bits and June peas.
Top with dressing.
Toss before serving.

title: yummy strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients as directed on box except substitute strawberries for water.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Icing For Yummy Strawberry Cake.

title: quick chicken and dressing
directions: Cover the chicken with water and cook until tender.
Remove from the broth.
Add vegetables and seasonings and boil until tender in broth.
Add cornbread mix and cook until like mush.
Add eggs.
Put in a baking pan and cook in 350° oven until light brown. This makes a real moist dressing.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and pineapple and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: velvet cream cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 9-inch layer pans (2).
Split each layer making 4 layers.
Whip frosting mix with cream and vanilla. Place between layers.
Spread top with thin icing, letting some drizzle down sides.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Spread refried beans in bottom of shallow pan. Spread mixture on top. Then add onions, tomato, olives and cheese. Refrigerate and serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Saute onions; add soup.
Cook until heated and blended.
Place broccoli in bottom of dish.
Pour soup mixture over.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Add enough butter to moisten crackers.
Cover top completely with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Dice cucumbers, tomatoes and onion. Add to spaghetti.
Add salad seasoning and Italian dressing. Toss together and chill.

title: italian bruschetta
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss gently.
Serve over toasted bread.
Sprinkle with grated Romano cheese.
Serves 8.

title: trifle
directions: Break cake into pieces and place in bottom of decorative bowl. Soak with sherry.
Drain peaches and place on top of cake.
Cover with prepared pudding.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain. Mix together beans, picante sauce, taco seasoning and sour cream in large mixing bowl. Add hamburger. Layer shell, mixture, then cheese. Repeat until out of mixture. End with shell. Top with cheese. Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: company pudding
directions: Mix together and place 2/3 of mixture in bottom of 7 x 11-inch pan; place remaining mixture in pie pan.
Bake together at 425° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 1 package of vanilla pudding and layer on top of crumb mixture in the following order:
thin layer of applesauce, layer of sliced bananas or peaches, then layer pudding and remaining crumb mixture on top.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: the smith's favorite supper
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Prepare frozen vegetables as directed in microwave.
Heat oil in frying pan or wok; add meat and stir often for 2 minutes or until meat is browned on both sides; add onion chunks and cook, stirring occasionally, 2 more minutes.
Prepare stir-fry mix as directed and add to meat mixture according to package directions.
Remove from heat.
Put rice on a large platter, leaving a slight hold in the middle.
Arrange vegetables around the edges of platter.
Put meat and gravy in center.
Serve immediately.
Prep time:
30 minutes.

title: cheaters carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Blend in blender 10 seconds. Flash blend for creamy. May use shrimp in place of clams.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain grease.
Melt cheese slowly.
Add all ingredients.
Use hot or mild ingredients, great both ways.
Keep warm and serve with nachos.

title: chicken and stove top casserole
directions: Boil chicken; bone out and cut into small pieces.
Make Stove Top as directed on box.
Mix soups with one can of chicken broth each instead of water.
Spread half of dressing in bottom of pan. Add all of chicken; spread evenly.
Add soup mix one kind at a time.
Add remainder of dressing by spoonful on top.
Let set overnight in refrigerator; take out 45 minutes before cooking. Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 55 minutes at 325°.

title: olivia's whiskey cookies
directions: *Or use 1 pound fruit cake mix.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and Crisco.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Slowly add figs and nuts.
Bake in well-greased 12 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° until well done.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine all, except egg whites and nuts, then add nuts and egg whites.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place in freezer.
Remove 15 minutes before serving.
Will keep to 2 months in freezer if well covered.

title: cocktail crackers
directions: In large bowl, toss crackers with oil.
Let stand about 30 minutes.
Combine dressing mix, dill and garlic powder or garlic salt.
Stir well.
Pour into bowl with crackers and mix well.

title: johnny cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan at 425° for 20 minutes.
Recipe can also be used for muffins.

title: chocolate "1880 cake"
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tomatoes and mozzarella with artichokes
directions: Alternate tomato and Mozzarella slices on large platter. Drain artichoke hearts, reserving marinade, and place artichokes in center of platter.
Scatter onion, olives, capers and basil leaves over top.
Drizzle reserved marinade over all.
Let stand at room temperature for at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
